title: low-fat tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna and peas.
Toss all ingredients together and chill.

title: wake-up biscuits
directions: Knead all ingredients together.
Let rise for 45 minutes. Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake until done.
Also makes delicious cinnamon rolls.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir in margarine the onion, green pepper, celery and garlic until onion is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes. Add more water if needed.
Stir in shrimp, heat to boiling.
Cover and cook for 10 - 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender. Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice.

title: appelflappen
directions: Blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix eggs, milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Core, peel and slice apples in rings.
Dip apples in batter and deep fry.
Serve with powdered sugar.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes with water; bring to boil.
Partially cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain; let cool.

title: marshmallow krispie balls
directions: In double boiler, melt oleo or butter, caramels and Eagle Brand milk.
After melted, remove from heat.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake in oven for 35 minutes at 350° or in microwave for 10 minutes in baking dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain and mash.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add milk, salt, vanilla and baking powder.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Add half of it to mixture.
Pour into baking dish. Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.
Top with marshmallows and brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling and pineapple in sheet pan.
Take dry yellow cake mix and put on top of this.
Sprinkle on chopped pecans.
Slice butter on top.
Put in oven; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Quick and easy; no mess.

title: 10,000 calorie brownie
directions: Melt caramels in 1/2 cup Pet milk (put aside).
Mix chocolate cake mix, 3/4 cup melted oleo, 1/2 cup Pet milk and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in well-greased and floured pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread chocolate chips over top.
Spread caramel mixture over this and remaining cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into iron skillet.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 450°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ahead and let stand 1 teaspoon vinegar and 1 teaspoon soda.
Beat together until light 1/2 cup shortening, 1 teaspoon cocoa, 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 eggs.
Add 4 ounces red food coloring (2 ounces is plenty and fill the bottles with water for the other 2 ounces) and 2 1/2 cups flour; alternate with 1 cup buttermilk.
Fold vinegar and soda mixture into batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter and sugar in saucepan; heat to boiling. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate bits and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch buttered square pan.
Garnish with nuts, if desired.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse with hot water.
Drain mushrooms and save liquid.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add seasonings and mushroom liquid.
Blend in soup.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until smooth and rather thick.
Add remaining ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until lightly browned on top.

title: bacon, chestnut appetizers
directions: I use Bull's-Eye hickory flavored barbecue sauce.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Heat until cheese has melted.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: squash stew(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Optional:
Sweet peppers, beef, rutabaga, beans, herbs, olives.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in large mixing bowl until well blended.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle pecans over filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: spicy crab spread
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients; stir until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve chilled with French bread or crackers.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Good for days.

title: potato soup with sausage
directions: Note:
If using skim milk, omit water and add extra 1/2 cup milk.

title: confetti rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper for 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Pour broth into 2-quart baking dish; add rice and stir for 3 minutes.
Add sauteed vegetables and cover dish.
Bake for 45 minutes and remove from oven.
Toss rice with parsley.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add flour.
Put into greased muffin tins, about 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown. Dough may keep up to 7 days in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Squeeze sauerkraut until dry.
Place in food processor.
Process until finely chopped.

title: braised sirloin tips over rice or pasta
directions: Melt shortening in skillet; brown meat on all sides.
Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add water if necessary while cooking.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into meat mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Pour over rice or pasta.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese pecan frosting
directions: Mix well and spread over cooked cake.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: In blender, combine peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and egg whites; process until blended.
In small bowl, combine oats, flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to peanut butter mixture and process with quick pulses, just until combined.
Stir in dates.

title: easy cheesy soup(30 minutes)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add onion.
Add potatoes and celery; cook 10 minutes.
Add California Blend vegetables; cook 10 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir to melt (10 minutes).
It's ready to eat.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop up tomato and onion. Mix together rest of ingredients and allow to marinate 1/2 hour. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in the order given and bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes a large batch!

title: pat's chocolate pecan toffee bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium-sized bowl, cream the oil and sugar and beat well.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Litely spray an 11 x 14-inch baking sheet with vegetable oil.
Press the dough onto the sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Let cool.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Spread the melted chocolate evenly over the cooled toffee bars and sprinkle with pecans.
Makes 48 (1-inch) squares.

title: tutti-frutti
directions: Mix water, sugar and cherry juice.
Dissolve sugar.
Add to juice.
Mix well.
Add sliced bananas, strawberries, cherries and pineapple.
Mix all together and freeze.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix egg, flour, sugar, salt and butter together and pour over rhubarb in unbaked pie crust and cover with a crust.
Bake at 300° to 320° for 1 hour.
If more filling is desired, use additional 1 cup rhubarb plus 1 egg and 1 cup sugar and small amount of flour.

title: lite fruit supreme
directions: Empty all fruit into a large container.
Cut peaches and pears into bite size pieces.
Dissolve Jell-Os in 1 1/2 cups of water. Add to fruit.
Thaw orange juice; add to fruit.
Stir until well mixed and put in fridge.
Stir well before serving.

title: terri's meatballs
directions: Fry bacon; reserve fat.
Mix hamburger, onions, eggs, bread crumbs, oregano, salt and pepper.
Form into meatballs.
Fry in bacon fat.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix soup and wine.
Put meatballs in baking dish.
Pour mushroom mixture over.
Crumble bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 6.

title: chili soup
directions: In saucepan, brown beef,
onion and garlic.
Break up meat and drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until flavors blend.
Discard bay leaf.
Makes 7 cups.

title: fresh apple cake squares
directions: Mix well together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples.
Sift together soda, flour and salt and add.
Stir in nuts and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Place in a 10 x 16-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until brown.
Let cool in pan.
Mix brown sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla in saucepan. Let come to a boil; remove from heat and pour over cake.
Cut in squares.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Roll fairly thick on lightly floured board.
Cut out and bake at 425° for about 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies should be just set and not browned.

title: snappy cheese(from jim curry's bar in lexington, ky, in 1946)
directions: Put through grinder the cheese, onions and garlic.
Add salt and pepper and work in beer until mixture is smooth.
Refrigerate overnight.
Beer that is not stale will cause mixture to separate, so will using an electric mixer.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Place all ingredients in kettle and cook until tomatoes are soft.
Put through food mill.
Return to stove and bring to a boil.
Pour into jars; process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Makes about 6 quarts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, egg and sugar.
Add butter and mix well.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into greased 3 x 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add some of sugar so white will hold shape.
Add remaining sugar, flour and salt.
Mix good with squash.
Add molasses, beaten egg yolk and milk.
Fold in egg white.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then lower to 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Blend mayonnaise, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa until mixed well.
Add vanilla alternately with water and flour until all ingredients are mixed in.
Grease and flour 2 round pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool; sprinkle top of cake with powdered sugar.
Serve.

title: short 'n' sweet caramel bubble ring
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle half of pecans in bottom of pan.
Set aside.
Stir together sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Separate each package of dough into 8 pieces, making 16 total.
Do not unroll.
Cut pieces in half crosswise.
Dip pieces of dough in melted butter, then roll in sugar mixture.
Arrange dough, spiral side down in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.
In a measuring cup stir together caramel topping and syrup; drizzle over dough in pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes (covering with foil the last 10 minutes to prevent overbrowning).
Let stand one minute only.
Invert onto a serving platter.
Spoon any topping and nuts remaining in pan onto rolls.
Serve warm.

title: dahm's diner chinese chicken chunks
directions: Mix soy sauce, sherry, honey and garlic.
Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch cubes.
Marinate in soy sauce mixture about 1/2 hour or so.
Before cooking, dust lightly with cornstarch and stir. Add oil to skillet or wok.
Stir-fry in 2 to 3 batches, constantly stirring about 4 to 5 minutes per batch.
Serve over rice.

title: banana crunch punch
directions: Freeze first 6 ingredients.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Can use 1/2 to 3/4 of a 2-liter bottle of ginger ale.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in pan.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt; cook for about 20 minutes.
Drain well.
In small pan, melt butter.
Add flour.
Stir until mixed.
Remove from heat and add sour cream and mix well.
Grate the cheese and put it in with the beans.
Add the sour cream mixture; mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs to cover the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute onion, pepper and ground meat.
Place all ingredients in casserole.
Mix water and soup together.
Pour over noodle mixture, then mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 3 to 4.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet hot slaw
directions: Coat a 6-inch skillet with nonstick vegetable spray and heat. Add all ingredients and cook 10 minutes over medium heat or until hot through.
Serve.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing and steak sauce together in a large bowl. Put in chicken and soak for about 4 hours.
Grill on barbecue grill until done.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on platter.
Spread bottle of cocktail sauce over cheese.
Spread crabmeat over the sauce.
Can be made ahead and covered with wrap.
Use toothpicks to keep from sticking.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook
and
cool
carrots.
Mix onion and chopped pepper with carrots.
Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetables. Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more.	Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: brenda's tuna casserole
directions: Saute green pepper in butter or margarine until soft.
Set aside.
Boil macaroni 10 minutes or more until done, then pour off water and put back in pot.
Combine with macaroni:
green pepper, pimentos, tuna fish, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
Stir until mixed together.
Pour in greased 16 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan and smooth flat.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
(Recipe can be reduced in half for smaller dish.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash
mixture.	Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and top with
remaining
cheese
in 8 x 10-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barley cheese soup
directions: Combine barley and broth in saucepan.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cook uncovered for 10 minutes, then add carrots and onions. Combine milk, flour, mustard and pepper.
Stir in broth mixture. Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir about 1/2 cup hot soup mixture into the cream cheese.
Stir until combined.
Stir cream cheese mixture in remaining soup mixture.
Stir American cheese until blended.
Top each serving with crushed red pepper if desired. Serves 4.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast (dissolved in water).
Mix with spoon until all flour is moistened. Cover and set in refrigerator until ready to use, then take out as much as you need.
Roll out on floured board 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut out and bake 12 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix together 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this gradually to creamed mixture. Add flavorings.
Dredge candied fruit and nuts with the other cup of flour.
Add the creamed mixture to this dredged fruit.
Mix well, then bake in a large tube pan about 3 hours at 275°.

title: crunchy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in mixture of flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Chill, covered, for several hours.
Roll into large balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in additional flour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not hard.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: country kitchen french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown meats together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on small party rye (2 loaves) and freeze on cookie sheet.
Put in plastic bags in freezer.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: christmas holiday wreath
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan; add marshmallows and melt. Stir in food coloring.
Turn stove off.
Add corn flakes.
Put in ring mold in refrigerator until cold.
Turn out on dish; add "candy berries."

title: toll house cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and hot water.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add to cream mixture.
Add nuts; mix well.
Add chocolate chips; mix well. Add oatmeal; mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry beef balls
directions: Pour milk or juice over bread.
Mix in beef.
Form into 12 balls.
Brown on all sides in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine. Drain off fat.
Whip cranberry sauce and vinegar with a fork.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles, or in center of rice or noodle ring.

title: spiced tea
directions: Add sugar to water and bring to a boil.
Add spice and boil until syrup is well flavored.
Cool.
Add fruit juices and strain well.
Serves 20.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Drain. Put in a casserole with 3/4 of the cheese, the margarine and the salt and pepper.
Let cheese and margarine melt.
Mix well.
Add eggs, milk and enough bread crumbs to desired consistency. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: crab with curried almond rice
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in saucepan; add garlic, tomato sauce, Worcestershire, Tabasco, paprika, salt and pepper.
Mix and cover.
Simmer on low 5 minutes.
Add flour; stir until blended. Add milk; simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add crabmeat; cover and simmer on low for 10 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Pour 1 cup sugar in skillet and cook over low heat to melt.
Mix remaining sugar, flour, and salt in a bowl.
Combine egg yolks and milk.
Mix well.
Beat into flour mixture.
Pour into skillet with melted sugar.
Stirring constantly, cook over med heat until mixture is smooth and thick.
Lower heat and add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Set aside.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add Bisquick and sausage.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into bite-size balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: celery loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Combine butter, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice in a small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until butter is melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oleo together.
Mix meal, flour and cinnamon together and add to egg mixture.
Add oleo, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to pie shell.
Bake at 350° until it sets firm.

title: zesty italian chicken breasts
directions: Marinate
chicken
in dressing for 6 hours or longer if you desire.
Take
chicken
out
and fry in a little oil until both sides
are	lightly brown.	Add a little margarine to fry before removing
chicken to platter or dish.
This can also be grilled on the grill.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and blend flour in, simmering lightly for about
a minute.
Add chicken broth and milk and stir until smooth.
Add Chablis and continue to cook on low heat.
Add Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and pepper and continue to cook on low heat until smooth.
Add cheese and stir until melted and smooth.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together the chicken, onion, green chilies and soup.
Soak the thawed tortillas in hot water for 3 minutes; drain.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place 6 tortillas.
Pour 1/2 the chicken mixture over the tortillas; sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: batter-fried apple rings
directions: Beat baking mix, egg and milk with rotary beater until smooth. Grease griddle.
Cut apples crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
Dip slices into batter.
Cook on hot griddle until golden brown, turning once.
Serve hot and, if you wish, with syrup, jelly or confectioners sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen rings.

title: frozen strawberry delight
directions: Cream sugar and creamed cheese together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add fruit and nuts.
Freeze overnight.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into the unbaked deep dish pie shell. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel pecan squares
directions: Melt 1/4 stick of butter and mix with cake mix.
Use pastry cutter and mix until coarse.
Press into a 15 x 10-inch pan with high sides.
Top with pecans (chopped or whole).
Combine brown sugar, sugar, butter and honey.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in whipping cream with a wire whisk.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 22 minutes or until entire surface is bubbling.

title: zella's five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings to sugar mixture, one teaspoon of each, and mix well.
Then gradually add flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour.

title: chocolate meringue kisses
directions: Heat oven at 300°.
Line cookie sheet with parchment paper.
In small bowl, beat egg whites, vinegar and salt until foamy. Gradually add sugar and vanilla, beating until stiff peaks form. Beat in cocoa.
Pipe or spoon batter into 1-inch mounds on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Place 1 candy in center of each cookie.
Press down.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until dry and edges are lightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: grandma gidley's soft white sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter. Frost or sprinkle with white sugar before cutting.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: shelly's coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in 2 pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into molasses mix.
Chill about 3 hours.
On lightly floured board, roll to 1/8-inch.
Cut out cookies.
Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Use raisins for eyes and buttons.
Bake about 6 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly and frost if desired.

title: zucchini raisin muffins
directions: Soften the raisins in the water for 10 minutes (lemon or orange flavored).
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Whisk together the eggs, oil and sugar.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Stir until well combined.
Pour into 20 muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes or more at 400°.

title: confectioners sugar
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender and mix until it is powder fine.
Can be used in many recipes that call for powdered sugar.

title: citrus crisps
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter, confectioners sugar, zest and extract until light and fluffy.
Combine the flour, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir into the butter mixture.
Thoroughly mix in the nuts, then roll the dough in waxed paper to form a log.
Chill in the refrigerator until firm, about 2 hours.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding raisins last.
Bake in unbaked deep crust at 350° until brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar with chopped cranberries.
Combine orange juice and pineapple juice and pour small amount over the Knox gelatine. Heat remaining juice and pour over gelatin.
Add cranberries and sugar.
Mix all ingredients.
Add chopped nuts, oranges and crushed pineapple.
Mix well and chill.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except fruit filling. Blend on low speed.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Spread batter in 9 or 10 inch deep dish pie plate.
Smooth batter toward sides, making a depression in the center.
Carefully spoon fruit filling into center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: coconut brownies
directions: Melt together over hot water chocolate and butter.
Beat in 1 cup sugar and 2 eggs.
Sift together and stir in other (flour, etc.).
Last, mix in 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 8-inch square pan.

title: mock oyster stew
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cover with cold water; add salt. Bring to boil and cook until tender but not soft (about 15 minutes).
Drain.
In another pan heat milk, butter and eggplant. Minced onion and green pepper may be added if preferred.

title: double decker dinner
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the first beaten egg, tomato juice, bread crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add meat and mix well.
Pat meat evenly in 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan.
Bake in 350° for 20 minutes; spoon off any excess juices.

title: herbed tomato soup
directions: Cook onion and butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, broth, tomato sauce, basil, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Place 1/2 of mixture at a time in blender; blend until smooth.
Return mixture to saucepan and heat thoroughly.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: calico salad
directions: Mix together all the beans, onion, celery and pimentos in large bowl.
In small pan, mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper-bring to a boil stirring until sugar is dissolved, let cool.
Combine all ingredients together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: lemon dream pie
directions: Mix by hand lemon juice and condensed milk until smooth; fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour half of mixture into each pie crust.
Chill and serve.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
for
egg whites.
Beat egg whites very stiff,
fold
into
ingredients.
Grease and flour tube pan and bake at
for 10 minutes and then bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: deb's chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mix the stuffing mix, water or broth and butter together.
Add the celery, onion, mayonnaise and salt.
In a large casserole dish, layer dressing, chicken, then dressing.
Beat the eggs and milk together; pour over the dressing.
Let set overnight.
Pour the mushroom soup over the top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Put grated cheese on the top.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: peking salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake well. Serve over salad greens, etc.
Refrigerate several hours prior to serving.

title: american chop suey
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Brown hamburger; add remaining ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Melt 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat until brown and tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining butter.
Turn up heat.
Add mushrooms.
Cook about 4 minutes.
Remove mushrooms.
Add Marsala to skillet; scrape bottom.
Boil 1 minute.
Add cream; cook until thick.
Return chicken and mushrooms.
Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: twinkie quickie torte
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer Twinkies (cream side up).
Cover with pudding mixed according to package directions.
Spread with defrosted Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath bars.
Chill 24 hours.

title: people chow
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter in saucepan.
Pour over chocolate chips and Chex.
Pour powdered sugar over and mix well (in plastic bag or bowl).
Put in plastic container or pretty Christmas can.
Makes a nice gift for relative or shut-in. Delicious!

title: pea salad
directions: Combine.
Blend together with mayonnaise.
Add a little mustard to make it more tangy.

title: strawberry slush
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Cover and slowly bring to a boil until clear.
Remove from heat and add strawberries, Kool-Aid, vodka and orange juice concentrate.
Stir and freeze.

title: microwave cherries jubilee
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, jelly, orange rind and rum, stirring to blend.
Put in oblong baking dish and microwave on Medium-high for 5 to 6 minutes, or until heated through.
Measure brandy in 1-cup glass measuring cup and microwave 15 to 20 minutes on High or until warm.
Pour brandy over cherry mixture and ignite.
When flame has extinguished, spoon over ice cream in individual serving dishes.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: festive holiday potatoes
directions: Pour ingredients into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Top with more shredded cheese and paprika and bake 10 minutes more.

title: sweet and spicy mustard
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, flour, salt and red pepper in top of double boiler.
Add eggs and vinegar, blending thoroughly.
Place over boiling water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add butter; stir until melted.
Cook and store in a jar in refrigerator.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar together for one minute.
Set aside to cool.
Stir in salad oil.
Pour vinegar-sugar-oil mixture over all ingredients.
Stir in salad oil and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin swirl cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Reserve 1 cup of cheese mixture; add pumpkin and remaining sugar and spices to remaining cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Layer half of pumpkin mixture and half cheese mixture over crust.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Make several hours ahead. Serve with cut fresh fruits.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: 8 medium potatoes peeled and sliced thin.
Put into greased 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Add 2 tbsp flour.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Pour 2 small cartons whipping cream over potatoes.
If this doesn't cover them add Half and half to cover.
Bake 350° 1 hour or until done and thick.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Mix and press into 12 x 8-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 375° and let cool.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add chili beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Use shells to line an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Before serving, top with chopped lettuce and tomatoes.
Serves 10.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake rolls, flattened, on a jelly roll pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Prick the dough several times.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise; spread on the crust.
Sprinkle veggies over the top.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: May add boiled eggs if you like.

title: shrimp saute rockefeller
directions: In a large skillet, fry the bacon rendering the fat.
Add the onions and briskly saute.
Add spinach, anchovy paste, Tabasco, heavy cream and breadcrumbs.
Cook over moderately high flame until mixture is thick.
Season with salt and pepper and Pernod.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: In a medium skillet, brown the ground meat and onions.
Drain well and set aside.
Lightly grease and dust a 12 to 14-inch pizza pan with flour.
Prepare batter by mixing flour, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, eggs and milk in a small mixing bowl.
Pour batter into pan, tilting pan until batter covers bottom.
Arrange topping of meat and onions over batter.
Bake on bottom oven rack at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Put on pizza sauce.
Add mushrooms, cheese and any other desired toppings.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly.

title: creamy mints
directions: Soften and whip the cream cheese with a wooden spoon.
Blend in the peppermint extract.
Sift the powdered sugar into the cream cheese, working it until it is well blended, kneading it with your hands.
Press into small mint molds or roll into small balls and press down with a fork.
Roll lightly in granulated sugar.

title: baked beans
directions: Rinse and soak overnight, after picking over, your choice of beans.
Parboil until you can blow skin off.
Cover with water and bake at 300° all day and add water as necessary, or, cook in crock-pot on low all day or longer.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook shrimp and scallops according to package directions. Cool in ice water; drain well.
Peel and remove shells and tails from shrimp.
Chop shrimp coarsely.
Cut scallops into fourths, if large.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Taste.
Add salt, if needed.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the pasta in boiling water until just tender.
Drain and reserve.
Trim mushroom stems; cut stems and caps into slices.
Melt butter in a nonstick skillet.
Raise heat to medium, add mushrooms and cook 3 minutes or until just tender.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan and parsley.
Reserve until ready to use.
Lightly grease a 2 1/2-quart ovenproof casserole.
Place 1/3 of reserved mushrooms.
Mix the 2 grated cheeses together; cover mushrooms with 1/3 of the cheeses.
Repeat layer twice, ending with grated cheeses.
Whisk together milk, eggs, paprika, cayenne and salt.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle top with breadcrumb mixture; bake for 1 hour or until top is golden and cheeses are melted and a bit bubbly.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sift together flour, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add butter, milk, pecans and vanilla. Beat for 2 minutes; pour in greased pan.
Mix together 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter and topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: wedding rehearsal chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken until barely tender.
Cool.
Remove from bone in large chunks.
Mix soups, wine, rice and chicken.
Pour into large casserole.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: aunt inez's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until barely brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugars and add oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin and mix well. Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to main mixture. Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream flour, shortening and sugar together in large mixing bowl. Add eggs along with beaten and mashed bananas. Stir in vanilla and soda. Mix well. Add nuts, Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Cut up ham, sweet pepper, cucumber and onion into cubes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well!
Refrigerate.

title: shepherd pie(quick and easy)
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add tomato products to meat and stir. Add heated drained beans to beef mixture.
Put in casserole dish. Put mashed potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Allow time to warm the dish in oven before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in pecan or almond pieces. Spread on any thin crackers (wheat crackers suggested).

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix and shape into 24 balls and press with thumb into tart pans.

title: quick and easy fruit crumb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit filling and press 1/2 into bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Add fruit filling.
Crumble remaining dough over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add milk and vanilla, stirring well to make a smooth creamy mixture.
Bring to a slow boil and then add butter.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: kansas dirt
directions: Crush the cookies and put half in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt the margarine and cream cheese, then add powdered sugar and vanilla.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Put crushed wafers into food processor.
Add coconut and 3/4 cup sugar.
Blend.
Add orange concentrate and blend again.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining sugar.
Freeze if not using immediately or refrigerate until needed.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well; roll in balls.
Dip in the melted chocolate and wax mixture.

title: home fries with smoked sausage
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
In skillet, brown sausage and onions.
Then add potatoes, salt and pepper and cook until potatoes are turning brown.

title: venison
directions: Remove any fat, soak 2 or 3 hours in salt water.
Drain, wash, then parboil for 10 or 15 minutes in salt water with 2 tablespoons vinegar added.

title: cheese barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients except buns.
Split buns; place 1/2 cup cheese mixture on each bun.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place under broiler for about 5 minutes or until well heated.
Serve at once.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix all with dressing, adding Chinese noodles last and toss lightly.

title: molded corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
When cool, mix in other ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.
Arrange with lettuce on plate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine coconut and butter; press firmly on bottom and sides of pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in pureed strawberries and lemon.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Beat all seasonings into the egg.
Dip the chicken parts in the egg and coat with cornflake crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Add stock to dish.
Cover tightly, using foil in absence of a cover. Place in preheated oven at 375° and bake, covered, for 1/2 hour and uncovered 1/2 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except half of the cheese.
Toss lightly until well mixed.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° until hot.
Before removing from oven, add rest of the cheese so that it will melt.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and boil first three ingredients for 5 minutes or until a soft ball is formed.

title: sauteed green beans with pecans and fresh tarragon
directions: Clean green beans and cook in boiling, salted water until tender, about 2 to 5 minutes.
Rinse under cold water and drain. In a saucepan, heat olive oil and butter; add green beans, shallots and garlic.
Toss.
Add pecans, tarragon and salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: dinner roll recipes
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, egg and shortening.
Beat together.
(Electric mixer may be used.) Add 1/2 of the flour.
Beat well and then knead in the rest of the flour. Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Form into rolls, bread, sweet rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes (rolls).
Turn out on counter and brush with melted butter at once.
Sweet rolls may be frosted with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: garden patch casserole
directions: Beat or blend cottage cheese, sour cream, flour, eggs, onion, salt, salt and pepper together.
Fold in vegetables.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Cut cake into three layers horizontally.
Place one layer on serving tray.
Stir crushed strawberries and milk into 1 1/2 cup Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Spread 1/2 strawberry mixture on cake layer.
Arrange 1/3 of sliced strawberries on top of cake.
Repeat layers ending with cake.
Frost top and side of cake with remaining Cool Whip and top with remaining strawberries. Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: juanita's california tortillas
directions: Boil chicken
breasts
in garlic salt water until done. Cut in cubes.
Mix
cheeses,
soup
and milk.
Add chicken to mixture. Lay
tortillas in Pyrex dish.
Place chicken mixture in center of tortilla.
Roll up.
Place tortillas side by side with seam side down.
Bake
in
oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle a
small amount
of	cheese	over tortillas and bake until melted.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs together. Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa together. Add flour mixture to butter mixture, mixing well. Then add chocolate chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet with sugar scooper. Cookie should be soft; watch closely. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: butter frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix together at low speed, then beat at medium speed until very stiff peaks form.
For a lighter icing, add an additional tablespoon of water and beat.
Keep covered with a wet or damp cloth at all times.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Warm ingredients and stir.
Put in mini crock pot.

title: baked squirrel 2
directions: Coat squirrel pieces with flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Brown in oil and remove from skillet.
Line baking dish with foil and place cooked squirrel in dish.
Add onion and garlic; sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Blend soup with a small amount of water.
Pour over squirrel.
Seal foil tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Open foil and add green onions and parsley.
Reseal and cook for additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Chop onion into the beef. Mix milk and oats together; let soak a few minutes, then add to meat. Roll mixture into balls; brown on both sides; drain.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients until boil.
Simmer for 2 more hours. Makes 8 or 9 pints.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries.
This will begin at once to congeal.
Add pineapple, bananas and nuts. When completely congealed, serve with either whipped cream or sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and dice chicken.
Place in a greased casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken and cover with crushed crackers.
Drizzle the melted oleo over the top and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreos (all but 4 cookies) on bottom of a bread pan. Melt butter and pour over cookies.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese with mixer.
Spread over cookies.
Mix chocolate pudding and spread over powdered sugar mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top. Crumble 4 cookies on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat concentrate in large mixer bowl with electric mixer on low speed about 30 seconds. Gradually spoon ice cream and beat until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth. If necessary, freeze until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes or until pie can be cut easily.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired. Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: lettuce wedges and beet dressing
directions: Drain beets thoroughly, reserving liquid.
Mash beets lightly with a fork.
Stir in mayonnaise, horseradish and salt.
Add beet juice, if desired, to make dressing the desired consistency.
Core lettuce and cut in 6 wedges.
Spoon on dressing.
(Makes an attractive salad.)

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and poppy seed.
Add milk, lemonade, oil and egg whites.
Stir until moistened; don't overmix.
Spray pan with Pam and fill 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine celery, onions, bell pepper and margarine and cook until vegetables are soft.
Cook shrimp in the shrimp boil according to directions.
Save the broth.

title: turtle bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups of flour, the yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Heat water, milk and margarine to 120° to 130°; stir in yeast mixture.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Sprinkle surface lightly with flour.
Knead on surface until smooth.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Grease cookie sheet. Shape 2 inch piece of dough into a ball for head, then make 5 walnut size pieces (4 for feet and 1 for tail).
Make a ball for the body with remaining dough.
Place body on cookie sheet. Flatten slightly.
Attach head, feet and tail, placing 1 end of each under the body.
If desired, press raisins into head for eyes. Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Heat the oven to 400°.
Make crisscross cuts in the body, 1/4 inch deep to look like a turtle shell.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 turtle bread.

title: indian-style planked salmon
directions: The centuries-old American Indian way of barbecuing butterflied salmon is an extraordinary treat.
The smoky, moist salmon is perfectly complemented with a chilled Chardonnay.
A beach site is ideal for this dish.
Originally the salmon was pinned to a split alder limb with cedar skewers.

You will need the following: a board about 3 feet (90 cm) long and 1 1/2 feet (45 cm) wide, a 5-foot-long (1.5 m) wooden stake, heavy-duty aluminum foil, 2 nails, a spool of wire, a hammer or a rock to drive the nail, and a wire cutter.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together melted butter and crumbs.
Spread in pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Mix and beat together sugar, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Spread over crust.
Top with pineapple and bananas.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Chill for 4 or 5 hours.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix eggs, cornstarch and sugar together; add pineapple with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linda's chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: best-ever basic chocolate chunk cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugars, vanilla and salt; beat with a spoon until fluffy.
Beat in egg and baking soda. Stir in flour, walnuts and chocolate chunks.
Transfer to a bowl just large enough to hold the dough; cover and refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours or overnight.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli.
Put broccoli, onion, soup, cheese and mushrooms in large pan and heat until bubbly. Serve with dip-size corn chips.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces under cool water.
Place chicken in baking dish (8 x 11-inch).
Combine barbecue sauce, pineapple and flour; mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.

title: sparkling eggnog
directions: Beat eggs until thickened.
Add sugar, cinnamon, ginger and cloves, then orange juice and lemon juice.
Place 1 cup in punch bowl.
Add ice cream and gradually add ginger ale.
Then add remaining egg mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and nutmeg.
Mix sugar and shortening.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook
potatoes	until
done,
but
not too soft.
Cool. Grate potatoes.
In
saucepan combine cheese and butter until melted. Remove from heat and add sour cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Fold in grated potatoes.
Dot with butter, chives and paprika.	Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli; mix all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
You can add 1 cup chopped smoked sausage if you like.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook sliced potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain. Make medium white sauce.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer in casserole (alternate potatoes and white sauce).
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pecan log
directions: Melt chips and stir in vanilla and milk
Add nuts; mix well and chill.
Roll into a 12 inch log on waxed paper.
Mark lengthwise with a fork.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white. Place pecans all over the log.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.

title: italian wedding cakes
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients until fluffy.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels with 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Pat in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Add strawberries. Let set partially in refrigerator, then spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well oiled hot skillet.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Add the Grape-Nuts and cool.
In a bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add salt, sugar and vanilla.
Combine with the cooled Grape-Nuts mixture.
Mix well and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Set the casserole in a pan of warm water and bake in a moderate oven until firm, about 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: quick cake
directions: Pour all in mixing bowl and mix for 10 minutes. Pour half of batter in ungreased tube pan. Add 1 bag (16 ounces) in middle, then add rest of batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool before taking out of pan. Very good! Freezes well!

title: pear relish
directions: Prepare pears (peel and core) and vegetables.
Grind in food chopper.
Combine other ingredients; cook for 20 minutes.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: save your husband's heart cookies
directions: Mix until well moistened. Spoon onto well oiled cookie sheet (I spray with Pam).
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove to cooling racks while warm.

title: swiss steak
directions: Using waxed paper, sprinkle paper with flour, salt and pepper one side of steak.
Lay seasoned side down in flour.
Sprinkle top side with salt and pepper and flour.
Pound with large knife or tenderizing tool.
Turn and pound other side of meat.
Cut meat into serving sizes, carefully keeping as much coating on as possible.
Just cover large frying pan with oil.
Brown both sides of meat.
You may have to do this in two groups.
When all meat is browned, return to frying pan and layer with slices of onion. Carefully add bouillon mixture and wine.
Reduce heat to simmer for about an hour, using egg turner to keep meat from sticking during cooking.

title: sweet and sour dill slices
directions: Mix sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over the first 4 ingredients that were placed in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Can chill the mixture to serve cold.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a large saucepan, combine soup and milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until blended.
Remove from the heat; stir in vegetables and chicken.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer three noodles, a third of the soup mixture and six cheese slices. Repeat layers twice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover; bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until bubbly.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.
Yield: 9 to 12 servings.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add almond extract, eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Mix well.
Blend in flour.
Drop by tablespoons onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter and pecans for 3 1/2 minutes.
Spread on crackers (in aluminum foil lined cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until it starts turning dark.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, milk, pimento, celery soup and mushroom soup. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dip chicken pieces in milk.
Then roll in onion soup mix.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice off cherries and pineapple. Heat until hot. Dissolve cream cheese and jello together. Add pineapple, cherries and Coca-Cola. Put in large mold or bowl. Sprinkle nuts on top. Chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until soft-ball stage (236°). Add vanilla and peanut butter, then beat. Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: sausage en croute
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes; unfold and roll out on a lightly floured surface to 12 x 11-inches.
Cut pastry crosswise in half. Wrap each piece of sausage in pastry, trimming pastry as necessary and sealing edges with egg mixture.
Use pastry trimmings to decorate sausage en croute, if desired.
Brush each with more egg and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and puffed.
Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.
To serve, cut each sausage into six slices and serve warm with a pot of mustard.
Makes 12 hors d'oeuvres.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine water, vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chewy fudge cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour
and salt in a medium mixing bowl; mix well and
set
aside.
Melt
chocolate and butter over hot water in top
of
a
double
boiler, stirring well.
Gradually stir chocolate mixture
into
flour
mixture.
Stir
in
eggs, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake
at
for
40 to 45 minutes or until a wooden
pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares to serve.

title: spinach salad with honey-dijon dressing
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl; toss well. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients and stir well. Drizzle over salad and toss well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place in buttered dish and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Dot with butter.

title: ham logs
directions: Dry ham on paper towels. Slice onions fine. Mix cream cheese and onion. Spread on ham and roll up. Space 4 toothpicks evenly, then cut.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Combine all but egg whites and beat well, then add egg whites and fold into cake mixture.
Pour into a well oiled and floured pan (dripper or 2 round cake tins) and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour and sugar substitute together until completely blended.
Add peanut butter and cream together until completely blended.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Spread margarine on slices of bread.
Lightly spread brown sugar over margarine.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of brown sugar. Broil until brown on top.

title: shirley's delight
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic.
Drain excess fat.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cook on medium heat for approximately 1/2 hour.
Add corn and cook another 1/2 hour. Delicious with cooked macaroni or served over rice.

title: double banana cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Arrange on bottom of pie crust the sliced banana.
Set aside.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine ingredients, adding enough Miracle Whip to taste. Best when sits overnight.
This recipe was given to me by the cook of a local restaurant.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place a layer of tortillas in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Brown meat with salt, pepper and garlic powder; add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Place layer of meat mixture over tortillas, then layer of tortillas, then meat mixture.
Add grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon with flour and water.
Add baking powder to beaten egg.
This mixture will be frothy.
Add immediately to salmon mixture and drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: wilderness pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with Dream Whip and pour over sliced bananas in crust.
Pour canned fruit (blueberry, strawberry or cherry) over pie mixture and gently blend into top layer. Refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: good and easy rice(servings:  8)
directions: Place in order in large casserole.
Cook in 350° oven for one hour or until all liquid is absorbed.
Stir occasionally.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Beat with a spoon and add 3 more cups of flour.
Grease dough and cover.
Put in refrigerator and let rise twice the size.
Roll out on floured table, spread with oleo, cinnamon and brown sugar. Roll and cut in strips.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: basic refrigerator rolls or loaves
directions: Combine 1/2 cup lukewarm water, 1 teaspoon sugar and 2 packages of yeast in large bowl.
Let rest 5 to 7 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons shortening in large bowl until "creamy."
Stir well.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water and 1 egg.
Beat well, then add yeast mixture.
Mix well, adding 2 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/3 cup milk.
Add 6 cups flour and mix well.
Let rest 5 minutes.

title: eldorado casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
Cook until meat is browned.
Add tomato sauce and olives.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and chilies.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole and layer ingredients in the following order:
Tortilla chips, meat sauce, cottage cheese mix and Monterey Jack; repeat. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mashed sweet potatoes
directions: Mash the cooked sweet potatoes.
Add margarine or butter and orange juice concentrate; beat until the mixture is smooth. Adjust the butter and juice concentrate until the desired taste is achieved.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, cucumber, green pepper, radish slices, carrots and green onion; mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine softened cream cheese and remaining ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Add to macaroni mixture; mix lightly.
Spoon and gently press into a lightly oiled 6 1/2-cup ring mold; chill several hours or overnight.
Unmold onto serving plate.
(Can be served in regular bowl.)

title: farina pie for shrove tuesday
directions: Warm milk and oleo on stove.
Stir in farina.
Cook about 15 minutes.
After cool, put in vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Grease pan. Pour.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue relish
directions: Grind the tomatoes and drain. Add the ground onions and ground peppers.
Add the vinegar to the ingredients which have been drained.
Add sugar, salt and mixed spices.
Boil 10 minutes. Seal while hot.
Makes 7 pints.

title: hawaiian spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving size pieces and place in a shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients (except pineapple and cook and stir until thickened).
Pour pineapple mixture over ribs.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 2 hours or until tender. Uncover and spoon sauce over ribs.
Bake 15 minutes longer to glaze slightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and egg.
Stir in two cups of flour.
Beat well. Stir in remaining flour (or enough to make a soft dough).

title: lemon chicken(serves 12)
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and lemon juice.
Mix together crushed crackers and poppy seed.
Place chicken pieces evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sour cream mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over this.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve over hot egg noodles.

title: spicy chicken jambalaya
directions: Saute chicken breasts in oil about 5 minutes and remove from pan.
Saute onion and tomato for 3 minutes.
Return chicken to pan; stir in rice, green pepper and celery.
Cook for 1 minute, then add water, bay leaf, thyme and parsley.
Simmer until chicken is tender and rice is almost done.
Stir in salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Place in casserole and heat in 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes until rice is done.
Remove bay leaf and garnish with bacon; serve.

title: a1 steak with tomatoes & onions
directions: Cook meat and onions until onions are tender.
Add steak sauce, tomatoes, and vinegar.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, and simmer until sauce thickens.

title: pumpkin bread(one loaf)
directions: Mix together.
May add nuts, raisins or dates.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Watch so they do not burn.
Do not double this recipe.
Makes 28 or 30 cookies.

title: meat-macaroni supper
directions: *Hot dogs can be used in place of luncheon meat.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Combine flour and yeast; set aside.
Combine milk, water, salt, sugar and butter; heat until sugar, salt and butter melt. Add to the dry mix and cover.
Let rise in a warm place for 15 minutes.
Turn onto a floured surface.
Make into rolls and brush with melted butter.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: german main dish
directions: Put a layer of potatoes in casserole dish, then add a layer of onions and sausage patties.
Then continue to fill baking dish, layering potatoes, cabbage, sausage, onion, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: quick bran bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add bran and dates.
Blend remaining mixture.
Add butter.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: non-cook pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all
ingredients,
except
Kisses,
in	a large mixing bowl.
Mix	on
lowest
speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately top each cookie with a candy Kiss.	Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: tuna roll
directions: Drain tuna and mix with onions and cream cheese. Roll into a ball and chill. Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Slice and serve with salad crackers.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; make 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Combine the vinegars, oil, garlic and black pepper in a large bowl.
Add the kidney beans to the vinegar dressing and toss gently.

title: quick 'n easy classic lasagne
directions: Lasagne cooking directions:
Add 1 teaspoon salt to 3-quarts rapidly boiling water.
Gradually add lasagne so water does not stop boiling.
Boil, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir gently now and then. Do not overcook.
Drain in colander.
Tip:
To hold pasta a short time before layering, drain and return to cooking pot.
Toss with a little corn oil or margarine.
Cover.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Cover and cook over hot, not boiling water, 1 hour until rice is tender.
Stir frequently during cooking.
Serve warm with cream.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Make a white Duncan Hines cake mix by recipe.
While it is hot use a knife and make slits on the top of it.
Mix a small package of strawberry jello by recipe on box.
Pour over cooked cake.
When it is cool, mix strawberries and Cool Whip and put on top.
It's better if it sits in refrigerator overnight.
Put fresh strawberries on top.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place pie shell in pan on baking sheet. Set
aside.
Beat
pumpkin, evaporated milk, molasses, eggs, cinnamon, salt, ginger and cloves in a medium size bowl. Pour into shell.
Bake
in
preheated
hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce
oven temperature to moderate 350°.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes
or
until
wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
to 20 minutes on wire rack. Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients: dredge dates and nuts in flour mixture.
Beat eggs well; add cooking oil, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 inch pans and bake in a
350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: summer chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion and apples for about 1 minute.
Add the curry powder, paprika and flour; continue cooking for 1 minute.
Add broth and mushrooms; stir until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add the cream.
Place chicken breasts in an ovenproof dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sage cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: black-eyed peas and tasso
directions: Cover ingredients with water and cook until done.
Real good with jalapeno added.

title: baked crabmeat
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch ovenproof casserole dish with vegetable oil spray.
In a small pan over medium-high heat, melt margarine.
Add onion and saute 2 to 3 minutes or until soft.
In a medium bowl, combine crabmeat, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cut into squares.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 as an entree (2 oz. servings).
Serves 12 as an appetizer (1 ounce per serving). Contains 121 calories per 2 ounce serving.

title: baked honey soy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, stir soy sauce, honey, vegetable oil, garlic, salt, pepper and whiskey.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange chicken (skin side down).
Drizzle with honey mixture.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Remove cover; turn chicken over and bake 20 to 30 minutes more, brushing frequently with pan juices.
Serves 4.

title: one dish fish
directions: Cook onion until clear.
Add fish, lemon juice, oregano, zucchini and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes (until cheese melts).
Serve right away.
Great with a fresh catch in the summer.
Enjoy.

title: prune bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Mix together egg and prune juice.
Blend with shortening mixture. Sift together dry ingredients.
Dissolve soda in sour milk; add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add nut meats and chopped prunes.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In a 6-quart pan, brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
The soup freezes well and is better the second day.
It makes a bunch!

title: spinach salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Toss lettuce, spinach, strawberries and almonds.
Blend rest of the ingredients and pour over.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain potatoes and pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add butter to hot potatoes and beat with a mixer.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and flavorings.
Beat at low speed until well mixed.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine water, margarine and onion soup mix in pot and heat to melt butter.
Pour in baking dish.
Pour in rice; stir to mix. Salt, pepper and paprika chicken and place over rice mixture. Bake at 325° or until liquid is gone.

title: cajun chicken gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken and season with salt, pepper and cayenne. Brown chicken in 1/4 cup oil over medium heat until golden brown. Discard oil.
Heat 1 cup oil until warm; add 1 cup flour.
Stir constantly until a rich brown (not burnt).
This makes the roux, which is basis for Cajun cooking.
Add onions and garlic; heat until wilted.
Add chicken and hot water and cook in an uncovered pot over low to medium heat until chicken is tender.
Five minutes prior to serving, add chopped green onions and parsley.
Add a dash of file before serving.
Serve with rice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: On a cookie sheet with sides, spread pieces of crescent roll dough. Pinch seams together to make complete crust. Bake at 400° as per package directions. Mix together cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise. Spread on cooled crust. Top with assorted chopped vegetables.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in greased 9 x 12 pan. Sprinkle cheese over bread. Beat eggs, salt, milk and oleo and pour over. Sprinkle bacon or sausage on top.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon of hot margarine, cook 1/2 of chicken until browned.
Stir often.
Remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups; set aside. In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, combine milk, egg and melted butter or margarine.
Add milk mixture all at once to dry ingredients.
Mix just until moistened (the mixture will be lumpy).
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon mixture into muffin cups, filling each about 2/3 full.
(Fill any unfilled muffin cups with some water for even baking.)
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.
If using frozen or canned blueberries, drain well on paper towels before folding into batter.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Stir over low heat until melted.
Serve warm.

title: date nut bread
directions: Stir dates in cup of water.
Add butter.
Heat to melt.
Pour in mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon to roll in.
Mix first 3 ingredients with blender.
Then add the water, flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix. Roll into walnut-sized balls and roll in the cinnamon-sugar mixture.	Bake 7 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Bottom:
Mix together oats, brown sugar and white sugar.
Melt margarine and pour over this mixture.
Mix with mixer.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: celery cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly.
Split lengthwise and place in enamelware bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add ice water to cover; let stand overnight.
Drain.
Put vinegar and sugar into enamelware kettle and heat to simmering.
Add celery and peppers.
Put in cucumbers and simmer 3 or 4 minutes.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars.
Fill up with syrup and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry angel food delight
directions: Boil 2 cups water and stir in Jell-O.
When dissolved, add 12 ice cubes and stir until melted, for a quick set.
Stir in thawed strawberries; fold in Cool Whip, pecans and cake (which has been cut in 2 to 3-inch cubes).
Cover and chill at least one hour before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat egg good.
Add sugar and beat some more.
Add flour, baking powder and pinch of salt.
Stir in apples and mix good. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brownish.
Cut and serve with whipped cream.

title: hekka(sukiyaki)
directions: *Grate 1/2 of an onion to be added to shoyu; cut rest of onion into slices.

title: funnel cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture. Beat smooth with mixer on low speed. Heat vegetable oil in deep fryer to 360°. Traditional methods of cooking: Pour batter in funnel holding thumb over end of funnel. Swirl batter in hot oil and fry about 3 minutes until golden brown; turn and cook one minute more. Modern method of cooking: Pour batter into a teapot with a narrow spout. Swirl batter in oil and cook as above. Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: ham and broccoli roll-ups
directions: Roll ham around broccoli spears.
Place rolls in shallow casserole dish.
In a small saucepan, stir together mayonnaise, flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until blended.
Pour sauce over rolls.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Broil 6 inches from source of heat for 2 minutes, or until bubbly. Serve.
Serves 2 1/2.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in 13 x 9 baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 375 degrees.
Cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Pour pineapple and juice in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour and cheese.
Mix well and spread over pineapple.
Mix butter and crackers and pour over flour mixture.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add Crab Delights and vegetables.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook 1 minute more.
Serve immediately.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line muffin pans with paper.
Set pans aside.
Combine grated apples, raisins, lemon juice and walnuts in large bowl.
Stir ingredients to mix well and set aside.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt butter and mix with cake mix and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Press 1/2 of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Pour chocolate chips over hot brownies.
They'll melt and then can be spread.
Put caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in micro-safe bowl.
Microwave on Medium or 3 minutes.
Stir. Microwave 3 minutes more on Medium.
Stir (should be smooth).
Pour over chocolate chip layer.

title: harvard beets
directions: In pan add sugar, corn starch, and salt with 2 Tbsp. of beet liquid. Heat over medium heat and stir until smooth. Add remaining liquid from beets. Then add vinegar and margarine. Heat until thickens. Stir constantly or it will stick. Add beets. Heat thoroughly.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix together and roll out.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Some specialty shops have bone shaped cookie cutters.
At Christmas, make holiday cut-outs and hang them on the trees for birds.

title: potatoes plus
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender.
Heat milk, margarine, cheese slices and soup together until cheese and margarine are melted.
Drain potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion over and pour soup mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat in medium saucepan. Add milk, coconut, eggs and sugar and stir until blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool or serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Store in refrigerator.
I add a few chopped pecans.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: In a bowl, combine soups, 1/4 cup butter and rice.
Pour into Pam sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces on rice. Brush with rest of margarine.
Season with Nature's Seasons or salt and pepper.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
(I used at least 1 teaspoon, sometimes 1 1/2 teaspoons.)
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender and rice is done.
Serve with a salad and hot rolls.
Very good.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat thoroughly on all sides, then remove from pot.
Add onions to pot; add garlic and saute.
Put meat back in pot.
Add package of onion mix to 2 cups water; pour over meat.
Cover tightly and cook 2 hours, adding more water if needed.
Simmer for the 2 hours.

title: light chicken marsala
directions: In a 9-inch, nonstick skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add chicken and quickly saute on both sides.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside.
In same skillet, combine mushrooms and garlic; cook over high heat, stirring constantly until liquid evaporated.
Add wine and cook, stirring occasionally for 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine broth and flour, stirring to dissolve flour. Add to skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add chicken, any juices remaining from chicken, salt and pepper and cook until heated.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Roll into walnut-size balls; freeze.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Hollow out French bread.
Fill with dip.

title: pork chow mein
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet heat oil, add onions and garlic. Saute but don't brown.
Add celery and pepper strips.
Saute until tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and bean sprouts, saute, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes.
Add pork and soy sauce and broth mix.
Stir.
Combine water and cornstarch and stir until dissolved.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Sprinkle with onions and serve over rice.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; stir in water.

title: apple and sweet potato bake
directions: Combine cinnamon, sugar and flour.
Peel and slice apples and sweet potatoes.
Grease baking dish.
Put in a layer of apples; sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Dot with butter.
Put in a layer of sweet potatoes; sprinkle with cinnamon mixture and dot with butter.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, horseradish, onion and salt. Refrigerate until firm.
Roll into a ball and roll in mixture of parsley and pecans.

title: potato-tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onions.
Mix together with soups (do not dilute).
Add to ground beef and onion mixture. Pour into baking dish.
Layer cheese on top and then put on top of cheese a layer of potato tots.
Bake in oven at 375° until potato tots are brown.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix beef, onions, pickles and crumbs.
Add a dash of salt and pepper and milk.
Form into balls, 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.
Stick a toothpick in each ball.
Makes approximately 24 balls.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Crush wafers and mix with melted butter; pat into a 9 x 13-inch spring-form pan, leaving a 1-inch space at top.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and brandy until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and 3 eggs, 1 at a time.
Add sour cream; mix until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Cool on rack.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and butter on High for about 2 minutes and stir often.
Spread into crust and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
