Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Slice up bananas and put them on top of chocolate.
Then put pudding over the bananas.
Top with whipped cream topping.

title: huckleberry muffins
directions: Sprinkle berries with a little of the flour.
Sift remaining flour with other dry ingredients.
Melt shortening; combine with milk and beaten egg yolks.
Mix dry and liquid mixtures quickly; fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Bake for 1/2 hour in a 400° oven.

title: french fried "flowered" onion
directions: Cut onions to form "petals," starting in the center.
Cut outwards in spoke-type fashion.
Cut down to, but not through, the root.
Soak in ice water for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain well and pat dry.
Mix ingredients to make batter.
Dip onions in batter; drain excess batter.
Fry in 375° deep fat oil until golden, light brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with Ranch, Blue cheese or Honey Dijon dressing.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Shell uncooked shrimp; leave tail shell on.
Split shrimp down the back; spread apart, butterfly fashion.
Dip uncooked shrimp into milk and egg mixture.
Next, dip in bread crumbs and paprika mixture.
Combine crabmeat, Worcestershire, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce, mustard, mayo and bread cubes.
Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons melted butter; add to crabmeat mixture. Firmly stuff breaded shrimp with crabmeat mixture.
Place shrimp, tail side up, on greased, shallow baking dish.
Baste with butter. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: german lace cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and stir well.
Drop 1 level teaspoon of dough onto greased baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining dough but allow only 4 to 6 cookies per baking sheet since cookie dough will spread during baking.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until light golden brown.
Leave cookies on baking sheet until just set, about 2 minutes.
Immediately transfer to rack for cooling.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil, also onions, garlic and chili pepper. Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and saffron.
Add rice and mix well with other ingredients for about 5 minutes.
Add water (or beer) and dry wine and cook on high temperature until liquid boils, then simmer until rice is cooked.
After all ingredients are added, do not stir.
Cover and cook for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and chip chicken breasts.
Mix with chicken soup and celery soup and put into baking dish.
Spread sour cream over top, then sprinkle stuffing mix over cream.
Melt margarine in 1 cup broth from chicken, then pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Pour cake mixture in bottom of a 2-quart ovenproof glass bowl. Put fruit on top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place into a buttered dish.
Set aside for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain well.
In baking dish, place ground beef.
Cover with A.1. sauce.
Layer onion, potatoes and carrots. Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: five week sweet pickle
directions: Put cucumbers in gallon jar with remaining ingredients.
Cover with vinegar.
Let stand 5 weeks.
Makes its own syrup.
Let stand overnight.
Pack in clean jars.
Heat lids and seal.

title: chicken rice
directions: Don't feel like cooking?

On the way home from work, stop at Golden Fried Chicken and get 1 bucket fried chicken, 1 pint mashed potatoes, 1 pint cole slaw, 1 pint gravy and 6 baked biscuits. Rush home, get paper plates and set the table. You will have a lovely dinner with no fuss and no mess in the kitchen to clean.

title: hamburger-zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add the beef; cook until beef is done.
Layer squash, veggies, meat and bread cubes in a greased casserole.
Season each layer with salt, pepper and paprika.
Top with the cheese; pour tomato sauce over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, peanuts, soda and salt; mix well.
Add margarine.
Mix until dry ingredients are moist (reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbs).
Press mixture into bottom of greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: arlene's great cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add flour and soda; beat.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook and mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Beat thoroughly.
Cool and refrigerate.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1/2 cup of cheese.
Put oil in pan.
Pour ingredients into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
After removing from oven, sprinkle remaining cheese on top.

title: texas pie
directions: Put sugar and flour in a bowl.
Set aside.
Bring to a boil the cocoa, oleo and water.
Pour boiled mixture over sugar and flour.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in jelly roll pan for 20 minutes at 400°.
Do not grease pan. Five minutes before done, make frosting.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with shortening.
Heat margarine and 6 ounces
of chocolate chips in a 2-quart saucepan; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except nuts and extra chips, real hard with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in pan with a rubber spatula.
Bake until the center is set, about 30 minutes.
Let brownies cool completely. Cut into 1 3/4 x 1 1/2-inch brownies.
Makes 20 brownies.

title: banana blueberry cream pie
directions: Line bottom of pie crust with bananas.
Prepare Dream Whip. Combine cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in Dream Whip. Spread over bananas.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa with hot coffee; set aside.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add to shortening mixture, alternating dry ingredients and cocoa mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This is good with 7 Minute Icing.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls or logs and roll in pecans.

title: french dressing(large recipe)
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until well dissolved, but don't cook. Add celery seed, mustard, salt, paprika and ketchup to sugar mixture.
Add dehydrated onion.
Beat on high speed and add oil; mix well.

title: beer hot dogs
directions: In a large saucepan, combine catsup, brown sugar and beer. Bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Transfer to a crock-pot.
Heat hot dogs.
Add to sauce.

title: fresh apple cake(for diabetics)
directions: Mix well in order listed.
Bake at 375° in a greased pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all in order given; mix well.
Pour into 2 Pam-sprayed loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake in greased casserole dish for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese and nuts crackers
directions: Mix with hands.
Shape
into
a roll.
Refrigerate until firm. Slice.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until browned.

title: tuna-potato pancakes
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water; cook until fork penetrates easily, but potatoes are still quite firm.
Drain and let cool while draining and discarding water or oil from tuna.
Grate potatoes coarsely, using grater or grating blade of food processor.
Gently mix grated potatoes, tuna, scallions, parsley, egg, salt and cayenne.
Form into 8 pancakes, shaping loosely but flattening slightly.
In a large skillet, heat enough oil for shallow frying.
Add pancakes; do not overcrowd pan.
Brown well on one side, then turn with slotted turner.
Drain second side and remove pancakes from oil.
Drain well on paper toweling.
Serve with Cucumber Mayonnaise.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hershey chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in pan over water.
Add marshmallows, milk and vanilla.
Stir until completely melted.
Cool slightly.
Pour into a prepared graham cracker crumb crust.
Let harden.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix
ingredients
together until well blended.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cheese and blend with sugar.
Add peanut butter and blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust and top with chopped peanuts.
Chill.

title: simply the best barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer at least 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes in large bowl; pour melted butter over potatoes. Mix other ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: vegetarian omelette
directions: Beat egg whites with fork for 2 minutes.
Fry onion in nonstick pan until transparent.
Add green pepper.
Add egg whites. Serve with sliced tomatoes.
Serves 1.

title: apricot-hazelnut cake roll
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper.
Set aside.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In large saucepan, heat sugar, butter and milk to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
If mixture becomes too stiff, stir in 1 or 2 drops milk.
Let stand until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen candies.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening; mix in sugar and cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between each.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add nuts and chips.
Spread batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Cut while still warm.
Makes 48 squares.

title: roast leg of lamb with garlic
directions: Day Before Serving:
Sliver 3 garlic cloves. With a knife tip, make small slits in lamb. Insert a garlic sliver into each. Rub lamb with olive oil and cumin. Remove leaves from 1 thyme sprig. Chop.
Sprinkle over lamb.
Lay remaining herb sprigs on lamb. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap. Place on platter and refrigerate overnight.

title: egg salad
directions: All ingredients are to your taste.
Cut up eggs; add minced vegetables and mayo.
Put into a salad bowl.
Add crushed potato chops on top.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until peaks form.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until meringue is stiff.
Spread over pie filling and seal to crust.
Bake in a 400° oven until lightly browned.
Cool in warm and draft free place.
Covers 9-inch pie.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 325° and grease pan.
Mix 1 box cake mix as directed.
Pour one thin layer into baking pan.
Let bake until the top of mix bubbles.
Add 1 cup sugar into apple pie filling. Stir thoroughly.
Put apple pie filling on top of layer of cake. Pour the rest of the cake mix over top of apples.
Sprinkle apple spice or cinnamon over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems from mushrooms.
Place caps in greased shallow baking pan.
Brown sausage; remove.
Saute mushroom stems (chopped) and onion in drippings; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon into caps.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then coconut and walnuts.
Bake in a moderate oven.

title: orange-cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Put juice and orange rind in measuring cup.
Add butter or shortening, then fill cup to 3/4 mark with boiling water.
Add to dry mixture.
Add unbeaten egg, cranberries and chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased pan for 1 hour. Let stand 24 hours before slicing.

title: mama's german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8 or 9-inch) layer pans, lined on bottom with paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot potatoes in half.
Scoop out pulp, reserving shells. In large bowl, using electric mixer, beat potatoes and butter until creamy.
Gradually add in milk; stir in onion, salt and pepper. Scoop mixture into reserved shells and arrange in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: date squares
directions: Use 8 x 8-inch pan, lightly oiled.
Oven temperature:
350° for 1/2 hour in metal pan or at 325° for 40 minutes in glass pan.

title: baked pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple chunks, sugar, flour and cheese in casserole. Pour juice over.
Cover with crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Make balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in confectioners sugar or coconut.

title: roman eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Dip in butter, then in breadcrumb and salt mixture.
Place on greased baking dish. Spoon on sauce on each slice evenly.
Sprinkle oregano and cheese. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Reserve caps.
Chop enough stems to make one cup.
In a medium saucepan, cook stems, onion and garlic in margarine or butter until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese.
Spoon crumb mixture into mushroom caps. Arrange mushrooms in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 24.

title: cheesy meat loaf pie
directions: Combine meat, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt in 9-inch pie plate.
Pat mixture against sides and bottom of pan.
Spread catsup over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheeses and oregano. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Drain and cut into wedges to serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: italian easter bread
directions: Sprinkle water over yeast.
Stir to dissolve.
Let stand until bubbly, about 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat milk in a saucepan over low heat until lukewarm.
Beat together butter, sugar and salt in a large bowl until light and creamy.
Beat in eggs; beat well.
Add yeast mixture and warm milk.
Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic; about 10 minutes.
Use more flour if necessary to prevent dough from sticking.
Place dough in large greased bowl; turn to bring greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place, away from drafts for 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead lightly.
Divide dough into 12 equal pieces.
Braid 3 together.
Place on cookie sheet. Braid 3 more and place on top of the first braid.
Place a hard-cooked egg in center of top loaf.
Roll a piece of dough into a thin rope.
Place over egg like a cross.
Cover and let rise for 30 to 45 minutes.
Beat an egg yolk with 2 tablespoons water and brush over bread before baking.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Brush with butter.

title: 4 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in stem pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken and cook broccoli.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish; lay broccoli on bottom, and then chicken.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Toss bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
In a small saucepan, combine milk and butter and heat through (butter need not melt).
With electric mixer at medium speed, gradually beat milk into flour mixture, then beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups flour or enough to make a stiff batter.
Cover, let rise in warm place until doubled.
Stir batter down and beat very well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan, 2 loaf pans, or 4 junior loaf pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake until golden brown. Cool on rack before slicing.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Grease tube pan.
Mix popcorn with candy and nuts.
Melt butter, oil and marshmallows over low heat.
Stir to keep from burning.
When melted, pour over popcorn and mix well.
Press mixture into greased tube pan.
Cover with foil to keep moist.

title: big mama's 24 hour salad
directions: Chop cherries; mix cherries, marshmallows, pecans and pineapple.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Whip the cream until fluffy; add egg yolk and mix well.
Pour over ingredients in the dish.
Stir well.
Squeeze juice from the lemon on top.
Stir, cover and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese and ham dip
directions: Combine all ingredients into a food processor and process until smooth.
Serve with crackers.
Keeps well so you can make it ahead of time.

title: purple cow
directions: Put grape juice concentrate and milk in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add softened ice cream and beat at low speed.
Serve immediately.
Makes four servings.

title: vegetables and beef
directions: Brown meat in large skillet and set aside. Saute vegetables in pan meat was cooked in.
Add meat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve over rice as is.

title: quick veggie soup
directions: Combine frozen vegetables, soup mix, macaroni, water and juice in a large heavy pan; bring to a boil.
Cook ground beef in a nonstick skillet or in the microwave until meat is cooked, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir meat into vegetable mixture. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to keep macaroni from sticking.
Yield: about 2 quarts.
Makes about 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: zesty stroganoff
directions: Cube sirloin into bite-size pieces and brown in hot oil. Remove from skillet; reduce heat and saute sliced mushrooms and onions.
Return sirloin to skillet; add tomato paste, 1 can water and sherry.
Simmer at least one hour, longer if desired, on very low heat.
Add sour cream and seasonings before serving, heating a bit to warm the added ingredients, but not boiling.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter; add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, milk, vanilla and baking powder; mix well.
Add flour and blueberries.
Evenly spoon mixture into muffin tin.
Sprinkle sugar on top of muffins.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy peach crisp
directions: Place ingredients in cake pan in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat calzones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Roll each biscuit between 2 sheets of wax paper, forming 6-inch circles.
Spoon 1 heaping tablespoon cheese mixture onto center of each.
Moisten edges of dough slightly, then fold each circle over (turnover style).
Use tines of fork to press edges to seal.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Place turnovers on sheet.
Bake until golden brown 12 to 18 minutes.
Serve as soon as possible.
Yield:

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients well, drop by the spoonful onto parchment paper. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix first seven ingredients by hand then add boiling water, buttermilk and soda dissolved in 2 cups flour. Mix well.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool.
Place layers of macaroni in casserole dish.
Add a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat layers. Combine milk and egg and pour over macaroni and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: yam candy
directions: Put foil on cookie sheet.
Salt and butter pecans.
Cook 15 minutes at 300°.
Turn off oven.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil; cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. (Start timing when mixture starts to bubble around edge of pan.) Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for one minute, until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into 8-inch square pan; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: crunch casserole
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, except the noodles.
Pour into long baking dish and sprinkle Chinese noodles on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
I serve over rice.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix first five ingredients and 1 cup crushed ice.
Just before serving add ginger ale and float sherbet sprinkled with the cherries.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as per directions.
Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and put in casserole.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients except food coloring.
Use medium heat. Cook until firm, but not hard.
Knead thoroughly.
Divide into 4 parts.
Color each a different color.

title: chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with mushrooms, carrots and wine. Spoon soup over top, spreading to cover.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: v-8 vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Mix all together.
Cook until desired thickness.
I add 2 or 3 diced potatoes, which I have partially cooked, then I add other vegetables.
I freeze part of soup.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Melt yeast in warm water and mix well with other ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and let stand for 12 hours.
Take lid off; punch down dough.
Put cover loosely on container if you are not ready to cook at that time.
Pinch of size desired to use and roll out on waxed paper and cut.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Bake in greased pans.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan melt butter in oven. Remove.
Stir in seasoned salt and sauce.
Gradually add cereal, stirring until all pieces are eventually coated.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 10.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Add pretzels, if desired.

title: easy no-bake cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese and condensed milk.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended, approximately 5 minutes. Add lemon juice and vanilla extract.
Mix until thick and creamy.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine whipped topping, pudding, pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and food coloring.
Blend together and chill.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together.
Beat 5 minutes.
Grease Bundt pan heavily with butter.
Coat sides and bottom with a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: In saucepan warm milk, stir in sugar, butter and salt.
In large bowl soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Stir in milk mixture and gradually add flour until dough pulls away from bowl. Add flour until dough loses stickiness.
Cover.
Heat oven to 250° then turn off.
Place dough in oven for 15 minutes.
Remove and place on floured surface.
Knead 2 to 3 times.

title: pie crust
directions: Put shortening in boiling water; stir.
To 1 cup flour, add baking powder and salt.
Stir in shortening mixture.
Add other 2 cups flour; stir.
Chill at least 10 minutes.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Heat applesauce and dissolve jello in it.
Add raspberries and cool.
Very good!

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients. Pour into pastry shell. Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer. Outer edge of filling should be set, center slightly soft.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread a layer of pecans on bottom of pan, then spread a layer of coconut.
Mix cake mix by directions on box; spread over coconut layer.
Melt oleo and mix with cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour chocolate mix in pan.
Cut with a knife or spatula to make circles in mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 7 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour in well-greased dish. Set before cutting.

title: fried pasta
directions: Thoroughly boil linguini (al dente).
Drain water and wash with cold water.
In a large frying pan, heat oil and saute garlic, pepper and parsley.
Add wine and simmer for 5 minutes. Finally, add linguini and stir constantly for 10 to 15 minutes. Can be served with chicken, beef, pork or anything you like.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Cook
potatoes	in
their skins, in just enough boiling water to	cover
them, until barely tender, about 30 minutes; drain. When
cool	enough	to
handle,
peel
off skins, they should slip
off
easily.	Cut potatoes into crosswise slices 1/4-inch thick.
Peel and cut apples, remove cores.	Cut into slices 1/4-inch
thick.
While
you
prepare
the sauce, keep apple slices
in	water
with
a	little lemon juice added to prevent discoloring.
In
a
small	saucepan,
bring
sugar, butter, cider,
syrup,
lemon
juice,
cinnamon and ginger to boil;
boil at	a simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain apples;
dry. Arrange overlapping
slices of apples and sweet potatoes in a buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Put slices at an angle, a
few apple
slices,
then
a few sweet potato slices.
Pour sauce
over all.
Bake
at
for	25 to 30 minutes until apples
are tender, basting occasionally with sauce in casserole.
Note:
All apples
vary
in
moisture content.
If the casserole
seems
to liquid,
gently remove some of the sauce with
a
big
spoon
or a bulb baster.
But remember that the sauce
is
delicious and that you will want to spoon some over each serving, so don't remove too much.

title: christmas sugar cookie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Sift the flour soda and salt.
You do not need to chill. Roll and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Melt shortening in skillet; add onion and rice until rice turns a pink color (about 5 minutes).
Add chicken broth and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes with a lid on skillet.

title: pineapple sticky cake(our family birthday cake.)
directions: Melt together brown sugar and butter in 8-inch round iron skillet.
Do not brown.
Place 4 pineapple slices in pan (I use as many pineapple as I can fit in). In different bowl, place white sugar, flour and baking powder.
Mix together in measuring cup the water, cornstarch and egg yolks.
Add cornstarch mixture to batter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Pour over sugar and butter mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.

title: sugar-free spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container or package into 3 (1 cup) gift packages.

title: sausage cheese tidbits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Parboil the chicken.
Break into bite size pieces; mix with sour cream and soup.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine and 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked fudge pudding
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to margarine mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir in the nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased pudding dish or 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Combine cocoa, brown sugar and salt.
Sprinkle cocoa mixture over pudding batter.
Gently pour boiling water over top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 25 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Calories/serving:

title: mamaw's marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until crisp, yet tender (about 5 minutes) in a small amount of boiling water; drain.
Combine carrots, cauliflower, onion, green pepper and broccoli; set aside.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Saute meat in 1 tablespoon butter. Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and next 4 ingredients.

title: corn bread
directions: Cook water and corn meal until thick, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 1 hour. Grease pan well.
This will keep in the refrigerator if wrapped in foil or in Tupperware bowl.

title: banana handfuls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in banana; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir into banana mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheets; spread in 3-inch rounds about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake in 350° oven for 14 minutes or until cookies spring back when touched with finger.

title: homemade chocolate brownies
directions: Mix ingredients and spread thinly in greased shallow pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together well and shape into ball.
Chill over night. Roll into finely chopped pecans.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make walnut size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove.
Put Hershey's Kiss in center of each cookie and bake for 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix chicken, Minute rice and broth.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with blanched broccoli florets.
Spread over broccoli the undiluted chicken soup, then the Cheddar cheese soup (undiluted).
Heat thoroughly in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut meat into cubes; brown in heavy ovenproof pot in a little olive oil.
Remove when browned.
In same pot, slow flame and brown onions and garlic.
Add paprika.
Chop tomatoes and red pepper; add with carrot, also chopped.
Return the meat to the pot.
Prepare gravy mixes according to directions; pour over the meat.
Bring to boil.
Cover pot and bake in a 300° oven for approximately 2 hours.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all the above dry ingredients in a large tupperware bowl. If time allows, let sit 24 hours, mixing ingredients by shaking the bowl occasionally.
This not only mixes the ingredients, but also distributes the seasonings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pour over ice.

title: amy's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Mash with fork.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well, except broccoli, cheese and 1/4 can onions.
If using fresh broccoli, clean, chop and steam a little. Put broccoli in greased baking dish.
Pour mixed ingredients over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Arrange cheese and remaining onions on top.
Bake until melts a little.

title: good cake
directions: Beat 7 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: In frying pan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until soft. Add chiles, broth, soups and chicken.
Mix and heat.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water in a large bowl.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add melted shortening, sugar, salt and nutmeg, if used. Add milk and eggs; stir until blended.
Gradually add 1 cup flour. Add remaining flour, beating until batter is smooth and satiny. Don't use too much flour, the dough should be soft.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix 1 minute at medium speed the eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add melted butter. Beat thoroughly.
Add cocoa and flour. Mix at low speed.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square dish.
Cook on High power 6 to 7 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 2 minutes. When done, top looks dry and will spring back when touched.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip together until creamy and smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Spoon cherries over top. Chill one hour before serving.

title: chocolate dipped creams
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Sift salt, cornstarch and flour together; blend into cream mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, then shape into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Dip the top of cookie into melted chocolate chips, then into the chopped nuts.
Cool cookies.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.
Cookies are very fragile.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except crescent rolls and crackers; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforated marks to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center and twist slightly to seal edges. Brush top with the reserved tablespoon of melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turkey a la john
directions: First, make a white sauce (Bechamel):
Melt butter over low heat.
Even commercial establishments have no substitute for butter.
Add and blend flour over low heat for 4 to 5 minutes. Caution:
Do not brown!
With a whisk, slowly add the milk.
Add the onion and bay leaf.
Cook and stir with a whisk or wooden spoon until thickened and smooth, approximately 20 minutes.
Add the wine, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Remove onion and bay leaf.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Combine the chopped spinach with 2/3 of the white sauce.
Put in a baking dish, approximately 10 x 14 x 2-inches and top with slices of turkey breast.
Pour remaining white sauce over turkey and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: heavenly pumpkin gems
directions: In large bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt.

title: ripe cuke pickles
directions: Mix together cukes, peppers, onions and salt and let sit overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a mixing bowl mix 3/4 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Roll in sugar-cinnamon mix.
Put biscuits in Bundt pan.
After all 4 cans are in Bundt pan, melt margarine in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Stir constantly.
When completely melted, pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn upside down on plate.
Serve hot.

title: christa's favorite chocolate cream pie
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Beat in sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in 1 cup of the whipped cream until blended.
Spread in bottom of crust.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook onion in skillet until tender. Add ground meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown meat.

title: very quick macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Then blend in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese(low-fat)
directions: Cook macaroni and omit the salt.
Drain.
Add milk and sour cream instead of oleo.
Mix to coat evenly. Add cheese packet and mix well.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: tart and tangy lemon bars
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a mixing bowl. Add butter and mix until well blended. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. The bottom should be 1/4-inch deep and the sides about 1/2-inch. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Mix the filling while crust is baking.

title: parmesan breadsticks
directions: Combine roll mix, yeast from packet, and 1/2 c. cheese in a bowl.
Add hot water and next 3 ingredients; stir until moistened. Shape dough into a ball.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Cover; let rest 5 minutes.
Roll dough into 16x12-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface.
Cut rectangle with a pastry cutter to form 16 strips.
Cut 16 strips in half lengthwise to form 32 (6-inch) strips.
Twist each strip 5 or 6 times; place on baking sheets coated with cooking spray.
Spray tops of strips with cooking spray; sprinkle each strip with 1/4 tsp. cheese.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85 degrees), free from drafts, 20 to 30 minutes, or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's chocolate pudding
directions: Scald the milk in a double boiler.
In a mixing bowl, mix cocoa, flour, and sugar.
Stir well.
Add egg and 1/2 cup of the scalded milk.
Add this mixture to scalded milk in the double boiler.
Cook and stir constantly until thick.
Bring to a boil. Cool.
Serves 4.
This recipe is easily doubled.

title: stir-fry chicken and pasta
directions: Heat butter and olive oil.
Saute garlic, onion and mushrooms until tender.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy; add eggs, then gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread into a greased 15 x 10-inch baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares after they cool.

title: perfect apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and milk in a mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour melted butter over sugar mixture.
Do not stir.
Arrange apple slices evenly in baking pan.
Pour sugar mixture over top.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: asian beef
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and red pepper; pour off fat. Add onion, green pepper, lemon juice, mint and beef bouillon; mix well. Meanwhile, combine rice and cucumber; keep warm. place about 1/4 cup rice mixture and 1/3 cup meat mixture on each lettuce leaf; roll up. Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ila's boiled custard
directions: Heat milk to boiling point in double boiler.
Beat eggs well; add sugar and flour.
Add this to milk and let cook until it coats the spoon good.
Add vanilla.
Let cool and serve with fresh coconut cake.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix soda and milk together; add alternately with dry ingredients.
You can use less spices if desired.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: To the melted butter or oleo, add graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour milk over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients except sugar together; set aside.
In processor, beat eggs with machine on slow.
Add in order the oil, sugar, carrots, raisins, nuts, then dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch or Bundt pan at 325° until done, 55 minutes in Bundt pan, less in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Frost when cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix everything except strawberries together in a pan.
Heat over medium heat until it starts to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove and cool.
When cool, mix in berries and place in pie crust shell.
Put in refrigerator until jello thickens.
Before eating, cover with whip cream.

title: chicken & dressing
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from broth.
Chop large onion and boil in broth until tender.
Combine into broth, deboned chicken, crumbled corn bread, chopped small onion, eggs, sage, salt, pepper and butter.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 400 F until hot and brown, then at 300 F until done.

title: spicy southwest tuna casserole(microwavable)
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine soup and milk.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Stir.
Top with chips.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix water, lemon juice, 36 packets Equal sweetener and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring constantly; boil and stir 1 minute.
Beat eggs, 2 egg whites and lemon peel in small bowl; stir in about 1/2 of the hot cornstarch mixture.
Stir egg mixture into remaining cornstarch mixture in saucepan; cook and stir over low heat 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add margarine, stirring until melted. Stir in food color.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cover
fish
with water and cook slowly for 20 minutes. Remove fish.
In the same water, cook onion and potatoes until onion
is very soft.
Return fish to mixture and add remaining ingredients. Mixture should not boil after addition of milk.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and bananas.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan (5 x 9 x 3-inch) about 1 hour at 350°.

title: south of the border stack up
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add onion, green pepper, seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish:
two tortillas, meat sauce and cheese. Repeat.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch-pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed of mixer about 2 minutes, until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Gradually add flour, mixing at lowest speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings, pecans and morsels.
Spoon batter into a ten-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool in pan ten minutes; remove from pan; cool completely in wire rack.

title: bob's new orleans barbecued shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in saucepan.
Bring to a slow simmer.
Simmer for 15 minutes and cool.
Remove heads and thoroughly wash shrimp.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Pour cooled sauce over shrimp.
Marinate for a minimum of 4 hours; maximum overnight and through day of dinner.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes on each side (until the shrimp are the proper shade of pink).

title: pasta di maio
directions: Saute shallots and garlic in olive oil until softened, approximately 1 minute.
Add sausage and vegetables and saute until al dente.
Add wine and reduce slightly.
Add cream and reduce to desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Toss with the cooked pasta.
Serves 2.

title: red and white delight
directions: Combine jello and water; stir until dissolved.
Add strawberries, banana, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into dish; let congeal.
Keep other half at room temperature.
Spread sour cream over the congealed gelatin, then pour non-congealed gelatin mixture on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits with the water until thick, stirring.
*Beat eggs in a cup and finish filling with milk.
Add to grits while still hot, stirring until blended.
Add cubed cheeses until melted. Place in buttered casserole; sprinkle with corn flake crumbs. Bake 30 minutes in a preheated oven at 375°.
(Leftovers freeze well and can be microwaved later.)

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix butter, sugar, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter together and form into small balls.
Refrigerate until cold.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler, stirring until smooth. Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper until cool.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar, milk, egg and salad oil in bowl. Mix only until dampened.
Break up sauce with fork and carefully fold into batter.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Soak
cucumbers in salt water 14 days.	Remove slime on top every
couple
of
days.
Weight
down
so	cucumbers are covered. Remove,
rinse
and
slice
thin	and
round.
Soak overnight in	alum water.
Rinse and cover with vinegar for 6 hours.	Throw away
vinegar.
Place
a
layer of cucumbers, a layer
of sugar and a layer of pickling spices until container is
full. Cover.
In	a few days the sugar will melt and make
syrup	to cover
pickles.
Leave in container or put in jars	and cover top. Do not process.
Keeps indefinitely.
No need to refrigerate.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place whole chicken in large saucepan.
Cover 3/4 way up the chicken with tap water.
Add onion, celery and seasonings. Simmer about 1 hour until chicken is tender when fork is inserted. Remove chicken from broth and allow to cool before deboning.
Test broth for flavor.
If not enough seasoning, add more to taste.

title: five (5) flavored pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo, shortening and sugar. Add one egg at a time. Add flour and milk alternately (add baking powder to flour). Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet and saucy meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in a baking dish.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Shred washed carrots and stir well with raisins and yogurt.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions, garlic and oregano in skillet.
Mix in mushroom soup and tomatoes; mix well.
Mash tomatoes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix skillet mixture, macaroni and cheese. Pour in
a	1 1/2 quart buttered casserole (save enough cheese to sprinkle on top).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken chimichangas
directions: Warm tortillas in oven or microwave until they are pliable. Chop cilantro and add to picante sauce.
Brush one side of tortilla with butter.
Lay on work surface, buttered side down. Place about 1/4 cup chicken, 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 tablespoon picante on bottom of tortilla.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces.
Sprinkle both sides of fish with salt and pepper.
Mix butter, lemon juice and onion.
Dip fish in butter mixture.
Arrange in ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Pour remaining mixture over fish.
Cook uncovered at 350° until fish flakes easily, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuff
directions: Pat out ground chuck in electric skillet to make crust.
Salt and pepper. Layer potatoes, onion, carrots and cabbage.
Add milk to cream of chicken soup.
Spread over top.
Cook on medium heat until hot.
Then simmer 40 to 50 minutes.
Melt cheese on top and serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut together; spread in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box and pour over nut mixture.
Cream the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together; pour over cake mix batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cake cools, it will crack up like an earthquake.

title: deer camp chili
directions: Wash beans and place in a pot with salt and enough water to cover well; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and soak for an hour.
Add more water, if necessary just to cover beans and simmer while preparing rest of chili.
In large, heavy pot, brown salted venison with 3 or 4 tablespoons of bacon fat or cooking oil.
Add garlic, onions and spices.
Cook, covered, until onions and garlic are soft.
Add both cans of tomatoes and beans with juice.
Bring to slow boil, then lower heat and simmer for 3 or 4 hours.

title: squash rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix 2 cups Bisquick mix with cooked squash (wet squash works best; add a little water if squash is dry).
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth.
Knead 5 minutes or 50 times; roll dough into 12-inch circle, spread margarine and cut into 12 wedges (like a pie); roll up beginning at rounded edges.
Place rolls with point underneath about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes.

title: kelly's no bake cookies
directions: Boil together sugar, milk and margarine for 3 minutes.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix together; drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Cool to hard stage.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut crust off the bread.
Butter bread and put in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, buttered side down.
Brown sausage and drain. Shred cheeses.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; set aside.
Mix the remaining 5 ingredients together in the order given.
Pour 1/2 of the cake batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Pour brown sugar mixture over cake batter.
Pour rest of cake batter into Bundt pan.
Take a knife and mix once through cake.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Make meatballs.
Then mix tomato soup, water, chili powder and brown sugar; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, salt, vanilla and nutmeg together. Add cinnamon, eggs, buttermilk and raisins; mix this into the above mix.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda into previous mix. Just mix until the flour ingredients are fully mixed but do not overdo.
Extra mixing tends to toughen the cookie.
Makes 8 dozen large size cookies.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter. Spread in 13 x 9 oblong pan and bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes. Cream Philadelphia cream cheese and add powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip and spread over cooled graham cracker crust.
Spread cherry filling over cream cheese mixture.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir real good.
Put in pie crust. Cover and chill.

title: chocolate-nut angel cake
directions: Add sifted cocoa
to
dry cake mix.
Prepare angel food as directed on package, increasing water to 1 1/3 cups.
After blending, fold in
chopped nuts.
Bake as directed on package. After cake has
cooled, remove from pan and serve with whipped cream.
(I use Betty Crocker cake mix; it comes out fluffier.)

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown chops with salt and pepper. Remove chops.
In same skillet, cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Add water, soup mix and sage.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add bread and stir until moistened.
Turn into a 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Top with browned chops.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions together. Add pepper and salt to taste. Fry sausage, crumble and drain. Mix in Velveeta cheese, sausage and a small can of Pet milk. Cook until thickens.

title: jog in a jug
directions: About 6 ounces at bed time.

title: zucchini cake with sour cream frosting
directions: In covered blender container or food processor, with knife blade attached, blend zucchini until smooth.
(There should be 1 1/2 cups pureed zucchini.) Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch metal baking pan.

title: banana pudding crunch
directions: In a bowl, combine milk, pudding mix and sour cream.
Whisk until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in bananas.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Refrigerate and cover.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Mix shortening, making crumbs.
Save 1 cup crumbs for top of cake.
Drop into remaining crumbs the unbeaten eggs, molasses, milk, spices and salt.
Mix until creamy. Add soda dissolved in hot water.
Add nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle top of cake with saved crumbs.
Bake in 14 x 10 x 2-inch sheet pan at 375° until cake leaves side of pan.
Great with whipped cream.

title: snickers
directions: Melt chips and vegetable oil in 2-quart pan on the stove. Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with foil.
Put in half of the chocolate mixture and refrigerate until hard.

title: white cake surprise
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool and cut in half lengthwise.
Mix pudding, powdered sugar and milk.
Add Cool Whip. Frost the middle of the cake with part of the frosting.
Spread with cherry pie filling.
Put the cake back together and finish frosting.

title: tuna stuffed tomato
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Stuff tomato with mixture and garnish with pimento.
Makes 1 serving.

title: wiener appetizer
directions: Bring all ingredients except the wieners to a boil.
Add wieners and cut to bite size pieces.
Serve with hot mustard and toasted sesame seed.
This is even better using 1 pound cocktail sausages in place of wieners.

title: tater tot casserole(serves 9)
directions: Spread hamburger over bottom of baking pan.
Scatter onion soup over all the meat.
Add all your cans of vegetables.
Spread your Tater Tots over top; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 to 2 hours.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400°, stirring occasionally, until golden brown (about 15 minutes). Press in bottom of oblong pan.
Save a few crumbs for top.

title: marinade sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and use to marinate beef, chicken or pork at least 1 hour before grilling.

title: custard
directions: Beat slightly with beater.
Pour into scalded milk.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a lightly oiled 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut butter into mixture with a fork or pastry blender until crumbly. Spread over fruit. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: daddy's peanut butter brittle
directions: Boil water and sugar in pan on stove.
When at boiling stage, add peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Stir constantly for 5 minutes, then turn stove down to low until thickness appears. Butter a plate; pour mixture onto plate.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Ready to eat.

title: cousin debbie's pineapple souffle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add pineapple and bread.
Pour into buttered 2 quart casserole dish or 10-inch square pan.
Bake, covered, 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until edges are lightly browned.
Excellent dish with ham.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: baked chicken reuben(1982 national chicken contest winner)
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken; top with Swiss cheese slices.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Pour
pineapple with juice in boiler along with Jell-O. Mix well.
Bring
mixture
to
a bubbling boil, stirring constantly. Remove
from
heat;
pour into serving container and refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Then stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Make cheese sauce by melting Velveeta in top of double boiler. Add milk and cayenne pepper to melted cheese and stir until smooth.
Fold broccoli into cheese sauce.
Place in a greased casserole dish alternating with cracker crumbs and melted butter. Finish with a good layer of cracker crumbs.
Dust with paprika. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Slightly beat eggs in sauce pan.
Mix flour with sugar and salt.
Add to eggs and stir.
Pour in undrained can pineapple. Cook until desired thickness.
Add butter.
Spread on cool cake.

title: orange date nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between each addition.
Dissolve and stir soda in buttermilk. Alternate adding flour and buttermilk mixture.
Add rind, dates and nuts.

Bake in tiny buttered muffin tins at 325° for approximately 20 minutes, or bake in greased and floured tube pan until a toothpick inserted into middle of cake comes out clean. While still hot, spoon over the glaze.

title: baked pumpkin
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar and vanilla pudding.
Beat egg yolks and add to pumpkin.
Add salt, vanilla and cinnamon.
Melt butter. Pour into pumpkin mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Drain sweet potatoes.
Mash and cook in large saucepan.
Add brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Cook on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and top with miniature marshmallows and pecan halves.
Brown marshmallows until light brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Break up lettuce in large bowl; add peas, hard-boiled eggs, crumbled bacon, sugar and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top; add chopped onions.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields 10 to 14 servings.

title: pork chops and peaches
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Lightly flour chops.
Dip chops in beaten egg and milk mixture, then dip in bread crumbs.
Heat oil in frying pan and brown chops lightly.
Place browned chops in Pyrex baking dish.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery in butter in a large, heavy skillet until meat loses red color and onions are tender.
Mix in soups (undiluted), rice, water and soy sauce.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; sprinkle with Chinese noodles.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Combine broth and soup and add to onion.
Add other ingredients.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat milk over boiling water.
Add rice and oleo.
Add sugar and vanilla to beaten eggs.
Then gradually add milk mixture.
Add raisins.

title: drumstick dessert
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
(Reserve some nuts for garnish.)
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: maple-coconut bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the coconut for topping and finely chop the remainder.
In a small mixer bowl beat 1/4 cup butter or margarine until softened. Add sugar and beat until well combined.
Add egg and maple flavoring and beat just until combined.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Stir in the finely chopped coconut and the nuts. Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine reserved 1/2 cup coconut and 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle over mixture in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: pastry for two-crust 9-inch pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour; mix.
Sprinkle with water.
Roll on floured board or wax paper.
Place over pie plate.
Crimp edges and cut off excess dough.

title: chicken wild rice salad
directions: Mix together rice, chicken, olives, celery and onions.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, Good Seasonings and mix well.
Add to rice mixture and toss well to coat.
Just before serving, add almonds.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken salad(g. c. a. a. salad luncheon)
directions: Add Miracle Whip to taste along with.

title: banana shake
directions: Put bananas in blender.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend 30 seconds.
Add ice cream.
Blend 1 minute.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and pinch of salt well.
Add sour cream; mix well, then add the pineapple.
Mix well. Cook in top of double boiler until thick, stirring until thick.
Remove.
Cool and add marshmallows. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled. This is a very delightful and refreshing salad.
Yummy also.

title: parmesan carrots
directions: Peel the carrots and slice them into disks 3/8-inch thick. (The thin tapered ends can be cut a little thicker.)
Put carrots and butter in a skillet large enough to contain the carrots in a single layer and add enough water to come 1/4-inch up the side of pan.
Cook over moderate heat, uncovered.

title: vegetable and fruit salad mold
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Cool until syrupy. Line bottom of mold with pears.
Place a cherry in pit of each pear.
Mix apples, pineapple, celery and nuts with Jell-O and pour over pears and cherries.
This can be made a few days ahead, if necessary.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil. Stir until moistened; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, undrained pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Remove from pans and frost.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with electric mixer.
Add vanilla. Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Add milk and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.

title: mustardy fried chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken breasts and dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a bowl, beat together egg and mustard.
In separate bowl, combine cheese and cracker crumbs, mixing well. Dip each breast in egg mixture.
Then roll in cheese mixture until evenly coated. Lay chicken on wax paper and allow coating to set for about 10 minutes.
Saute chicken on both sides in heated oil for about 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Add oil if needed.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen banana split dessert(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and butter. Add sugar and milk. Cook at a rolling boil for 8 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and cool. Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs. Cover with bananas. Slice ice cream and place over bananas. Cover with cooled chocolate sauce. Freeze. Serve with whipped cream and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Serves 12 to 16.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Stir sugar into rhubarb.
Add oil with beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients all at once.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with some cinnamon and sprinkle on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.
Do not freeze.

title: fried apples
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Open can of apples and put in a casserole dish.
Using a brisk motion, tap pan on tabletop to evenly distribute apples in pan.
Note:
Refrain from stirring unnecessarily during fried apple preparation.
Stir only when recipe says to stir.
Pour sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour evenly over apples.
Cut margarine in pieces.
Dot on top of apples evenly.
Place in oven uncovered 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Stir gently.
Return to oven 5 minutes more.

title: vanilla tofu ice cream
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup water in blender for 5 minutes. Whiz briefly.
Add
cup boiling water and blend to dissolve gelatin. Add
cashews and blend smooth.
Add remaining ingredients
and blend,
gradually
adding
ice
cubes with water. Blend
well. Freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes prior to serving for easier scooping.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside. Roll out biscuits individually.
Pour sugar mixture on top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Roll each biscuit cut diagonally.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Steam clams and pry open.
Drain off and measure liquid; there should be 1 cup.
Put the carrot, potatoes and celery into the chicken broth.
Cover and boil gently until tender.
Then cut clams finely with sharp kitchen scissors.
Saute the clams and onion in the butter for 5 minutes.
Blend flour evenly into this mixture. Add broth and vegetables gradually, stirring constantly to keep smooth.
Add the clam broth, cream and seasonings.
Heat just to boiling and serve immediately.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: cheese and sausage omelet
directions: In an 8 x 9-inch square pan, place bread on bottom.
Brown sausage and drain.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs and cheese.
Add milk, sausage, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dumplings
directions: Put the cottage cheese in bowl and break up with a fork.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add flour and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Form into balls with moist hands.
Drop into 2 quarts of slightly boiling water and cook, covered, for 20 minutes at a gentle boil. Remove from water with slotted spoon and drain.
Roll in browned buttered crumbs and serve hot with main meat.

title: angel food supreme
directions: With two forks, carefully remove inside of cake, leaving firm shell.
Tear these in small pieces and blend with whipped cream, coconut, pineapple and cut marshmallows.
Fill ring and put in refrigerator for several hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for approximately 25 minutes. Yields 18 muffins.

title: honey walnut bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in honey and sugar.
Stir over low heat until sugar is melted.
In a large bowl at slow speed, beat in egg yolks and soft butter.
Add in thirds the flour with salt and soda; beat 2 minutes.
Add chopped nuts; mix and pour in bread tin.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 5 minutes in greased and floured pan. Let stand 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Place over bread broken up in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and add milk, mustard, seasoned salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over rest of casserole and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix jello
according to directions so it is just starting to set.
Mix softened cream cheese and pineapple so cheese will not be lumpy.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend butter and sugars.
Mix well. Add flour, oats, baking soda and salt in separate bowl.
Add vanilla and egg to butter and sugar.
Blend, gradually adding dry mixture.
Blend well.
Add raisins.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet by the teaspoon.
Bake 12 minutes.
Let cool before removing.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears (unpeeled), peppers and onions coarsely; drain. Add other ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Cook jars for 10 minutes to be sure they are sealed.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons flour and salt and dredge meat through it.
Heat skillet; add 2 tablespoons of butter and meat.
Brown meat quickly.
In separate frying pan, saute mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter and flour.
Add tomato paste and stir together until it thickens.
Add meat stock or can beef broth into mixture.
Add meat to frying pan and stir in sour cream.
Heat briefly and serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and let set overnight, then drain.
Mix the next 3 ingredients until sugar dissolves. Pour over cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Keep in refrigerator. (Do not heat.)

title: chi chi
directions: Mix well and serve chilled.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine.
Rinse with cold water and set aside.
Heat oil. Add onion and garlic and cook until soft (about 5 minutes).
Blend in flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Add wine and cook for 2 minutes.
Add clam juice and broth.
Cook for 4 minutes. Stir in clams and cheese.
Add noodles and toss well.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix herbs with the meat; form into balls.
Roll in seasoned flour; fry until browned.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and spices; stir in candied fruit and nuts.
Add Karo syrup, sugar, lemon juice and rind to beaten egg; mix well.
Stir in flour-fruit mixture.
Divide dough in half; turn out onto well-greased and floured baking sheets. Moisten hands; flatten dough to 1/8-inch thickness (dough will rise during baking).
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned and firm to the touch.
Remove from oven.
Immediately brush with thin icing made with confectioners sugar and water.
Cut into shapes while still warm. Remove from pan.
Decorate with cutouts or colored icing.
Cover tightly; store to mellow.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Lightly spray a cookie sheet with cooking spray.

title: easy barbecue
directions: Mix hamburg, onion, salt and pepper; brown.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over drained hamburg.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with honey graham crackers. Mix instant pudding with milk and Cool Whip.
Pour on top of grahams.
Let set up (in refrigerator) for 10 minutes.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top.
Let set for 10 minutes, again in refrigerator.
Ice with Pillsbury milk chocolate icing.
Keep chilled for several hours before serving.

title: marinated grilled chicken breast
directions: Mix first five ingredients, heat until warm and butter melted. Completely cool and add chicken breasts.
Marinate 2 hours.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat egg, then add milk and dry ingredients. Stir until smooth.
Use a funnel or spoon to drop into hot oil at 360°.
If batter is too thick for funnel, add small amount of milk for desired consistency.
Fry until lightly browned on both sides. Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: monkey bread ii
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag. Add biscuit pieces to cinnamon and sugar mixture until well covered. Layer biscuit pieces into a greased Bundt cake pan. Boil the brown sugar and margarine for 1 minute. Pour brown sugar mixture over biscuit pieces. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes, then flip over onto plate. Use fingers to eat.

title: microwave "oven-fried" chicken
directions: Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken. Arrange pieces, skin side up, in 12 x 8 x 2-inch microwavable dish, with thickest parts to outside edges.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High (100%) for 10 minutes; rotate dish 1/2 turn. Microwave on High until done, 8 to 12 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: Make crust with graham cracker crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press into bottom of baking pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk. Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over bananas.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Refrigerate about 3 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding mix, pecans, marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip and chill for 1 hour.

title: purple cow shakes
directions: Cover and blend on high speed 30 seconds.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
(The mixture will be crumbly.)
Sprinkle over top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks. Add remainder of ingredients until well blended.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Place pie shell on oven rack and pour in filling. Bake 45 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: tasty cake
directions: Grease and flour large cookie sheet.
Mix first 8 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; while warm, spread with peanut butter.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon-pecan dainties(cookies)
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, lemon peel and lemon juice; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts.

title: fabulous cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat cream cheese with cottage cheese until creamy and well combined.
At low speed, beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add melted margarine and sour cream.
Beat just until smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around edges of cake. Turn off oven.
Let cake stand in oven for 2 hours.
Remove cake from oven and let cool completely.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Run knife around edges to loosen.
Remove sides of pan, but leave bottom in place.
Spoon fruit over top.
Cake may be frozen before adding fruit topping.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: alfredo's mystery pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans over cream cheese mixture.
Beat eggs only until blended; add sugar, corn syrup and vanilla and blend well. Gently pour corn syrup mixture over pecans.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Then turn oven down to 350° and cook until center is firm to touch.

title: quick corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir into corn.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add melted butter last.
Pour into greased pan, 8 x 8 1/2-inch.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast on waxed paper.
Carefully flatten chicken by using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 slice of ham and cheese on each chicken breast, tuck in sides and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Secure with toothpicks.
Beat egg and water together.
Combine bread crumbs, flour and Parmesan cheese.
Dip each piece of chicken into the egg mixture and then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Brown chicken in hot cooking oil.
Drain.
Reserve pan drippings for Creamy Sauce.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa together.
In large bowl cream sugar, flour and eggs together.
Add cocoa mixture; add pecans and coconut. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and while cake is still hot spread marshmallow cream on top.
While your cake is baking, prepare icing.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Heat.
Serve hot in punch cups.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.
Great on a cold evening.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix filling ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon over chicken.
Add celery, onion, salt, pepper, pimento and mayonnaise; toss.
Toss with grapes.
Hold almonds until last.
Cover and chill (overnight is better but not required).
Toss in almonds just before serving.
Serve inside cantaloupe slices.

title: summer salad
directions: Mash cheese with fork (3 tablespoons of cottage cheese can be substituted).
Whip cream; add cheese and nuts.
Mix, then add pineapple to whipped Jell-O.
Chill until firm.
Mix lemon Jell-O and let firm slightly and add on top of other ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: rice st. paul
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Add soup, water and rice.
Cook 7 minutes.
Add bell pepper, onions, celery and almonds.
Mix well. Put in 9 x 15-inch casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 20 to 30 more minutes until brown.

title: i don't know the name cupcake
directions: Melt together the butter and chocolate chips.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for exactly 20 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add sugar, gelatin and marshmallows and bring to boil until marshmallows are dissolved.
Set in refrigerator until just begins to thicken.
Remove and fold in cottage cheese, pineapple, nuts and whipped topping.
Return to refrigerator until firm.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Reserving 2 cups of crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Bone chicken.
Chop coarsely and add remaining ingredients except soup.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Baste with soup while cooking in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: basic muffins
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Butter a 6-cup muffin pan.
Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Melt the butter.
Mix together the milk, egg and melted butter.
Stir the milk mixture into the flour mixture until combined but still lumpy, just 15 to 20 seconds.
Pour into the buttered pan and bake in the preheated oven until it is lightly browned, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza strata
directions: Advance Preparation:
Remove crusts from 4 slices bread; reserve crusts.
Use remaining 4 slices of bread and crusts to cover bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In skillet cook sausage and onion 10 minutes or until sausage is brown. Drain.
Spread meat-onion mixture over bread in baking dish. Cover meat with sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Spread pizza sauce over cheese.
Cut remaining 4 slices bread on the diagonal; place in 2 rows atop sauce.
(Bases should overlap points of preceding triangles.)
Combine eggs, milk, parsley and oregano.
Pour over bread.
Cover tightly; chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix together.
Float sliced oranges and strawberries on top.

title: maye's applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until batter is thick.
Grease 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a flat baking dish and place in a slow oven (300°) and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is perfectly tender and pudding is thick and creamy, not dry.
Stir every 15 minutes with a fork, carefully turning the brown top and scraping the edges down.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 5 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust, then top with pie filling.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: halloween recipe
directions: Cut off top of oranges; scoop out orange pulp, leaving shell. Cut Jack-O-Lantern faces in each orange.
Use scissors (it's easier).
Cut holes in each top.
Fill each shell with ice cream. Put top on each orange and stick the cinnamon stick in hole. Freeze for at least 3 hours.
Serve!
Great for parties! Children can help.

title: hot chicken salad
