directions: Mix together and place in casserole. Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups crushed potato chips and 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese over casserole. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken-cucumber salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Rinse under running cold water; drain.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Toss with macaroni, chicken and cucumber.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve in lettuce cups and garnish with paprika and snipped parsley if desired.

title: chicken stir-fry with soy sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Stir-fry chicken in oil until cooked through.
Add vegetables and stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture, cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine and bake in casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ima's tater candy
directions: Peel tater 'n mash thru a sieve...slowly add sugah while tater iz still hot...keep this heah up til you've got a stiff dough.
Roll this betwixt 2 sheets uv wax papur to bout 1/4-inch thickness...spread
wid a layer uv peanut buttah 'n roll up lak you duz a jelly roll...chill 'n slice.

title: fresh blueberry scones
directions: Mix first three ingredients together lightly; set aside. Sift flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt together; cut in butter. Break eggs into glass measuring cup; beat with fork.
Add enough cream to make 2/3 c. liquid.
Lightly stir egg mixture and berries into dry ingredients.
Handle dough as little as possible.
Turn dough out onto floured board; divide into two portions. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Pat each dough portion into a circle 6 inches across and 3/4 inch thick.
Score each into 6 wedges.

title: spanakopita
directions: Saute onion and garlic, in skillet sprayed with Pam, until tender (3 minutes).
Combine with spinach, cheese and next 6 ingredients; stir well.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon in hot grease. Brown on both sides.

title: mexican cheese soup
directions: In a medium saucepan cook onion, carrots and celery in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, paprika, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce until blended.
Add chicken broth and milk. Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in liquid smoke.
Reduce heat to very low, then stir in cheese. Simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle soup in bowls; top soup with chopped chilies and 4 or 5 tortilla chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked cauliflower meat loaf
directions: Wash cauliflower, divide into flowerets, cook for 15 minutes and drain.
Mix ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper.
Put this mixture in a greased round baking dish.
Put cauliflower on top.
Melt butter, add flour, stir and add milk. Let mixture boil 5 minutes.
Add cheese and lemon juice, cook on low heat until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over cauliflower. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place tomatoes around cauliflower and bake 10 more minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: karen's potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine and mix rest of ingredients.
Put in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide in 4 or 5 rolls. Wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator and use as desired.
Cut each roll into slices and bake in moderate oven until crisp, 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles and bread crumbs. Alternate layers of meat mixture with noodles in 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake for 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: tuna dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients together.
Chill before serving.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: spinach dip in the "round"
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, squeezing out excess moisture.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight or several hours to combine flavors. Right before serving, scoop out large area in center of bread, cutting/tearing center into small pieces.
Spoon dip into center and arrange pieces around bread ring.
(If necessary, can cube loaf of French bread for extra pieces.) Serves 25 at party.

title: roast pork loin
directions: Trim fat off pork loin.
With
a sharp knife, make deep slits in meat.
Insert
garlic
and rosemary or fennel leaves. Rub outside of meat well with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in roasting pan with
wine.
Roast,
uncovered,
in
350° oven until tender, allowing 40 minutes per pound.
Baste meat as it roasts, adding more wine if needed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dump it cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump applesauce into it.
Dump pineapple on top of that.
Spread cake mix (dry) over that.
Melt margarine and pour on top of the cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over the butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip or cream.

title: twenty minute soup
directions: Boil vegetables until tender in 1/2-cup water.
Save the water and add 1 can chicken broth; add Northern beans, salt and pepper; cook 10 minutes.
If more soup is desired, add 1 more can of broth and 1/2 bouillon cube.
Also can add zucchini or any other vegetable or noodles rather than beans.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: champagne strawberry soup
directions: Puree strawberries and sugar in blender until smooth; press mixture through sieve.
Lightly whisk in cream and cinnamon. Chill completely.

title: fruit salad topping
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until thick.
Add the butter, salt and marshmallows.
Let this cool overnight and then add the whipped cream.
Serve with bowl of mixed fruit salad.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Scald milk. Add shortening and sugar. Cool to 115° and then add yeast and 4 cups sifted flour and beat. Let rise.

title: homemade churned ice cream("can always add desired flavor")
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk slowly.
Then add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
You may add any fruit you like halfway through the churning.
(That way the fruit does not settle down to the bottom.)

title: farm baked ham slices
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine dry pie crust mix with mustard and sage.
Prepare according to package directions.
Roll pastry into 16 to 17-inch square.
Drain ham and wipe dry.
Place in center of pastry.
Wrap as you would a package. Moisten edges with cold water and press together firmly to seal.
Place seam side down on a greased baking sheet.
Brush with egg.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake one hour, or until browned.

title: pressed sylte (swedish christmas meat)
directions: Boil pork and veal separately in salted water until very tender.
To 2 cups of veal stock, add spices, salt and pepper to taste.
Boil 5 minutes.
Strain and mix with meat that has been cut into tiny cubes.
Let stand until cool.
Put in deep loaf pan lined with cheesecloth.
Place weight on top of pan.
Keep in refrigerator.
After cooled and jellied, cheesecloth can be removed and loaf wrapped in foil until ready to use.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chicken in bottom.
Mix soups and milk together; pour over chicken.
Melt butter into broth.
Put dry stuffing with seasoning over mixture.
Pour butter/broth over stuffing.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion in a large pan. Add the water, taco seasoning, tomato sauce, corn and kidney beans.
Simmer about 30 minutes until warm. Top with shredded cheese, Doritos and sour cream.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix.
Pour into greased and floured pans, 1 large loaf pan, Bundt pan or 3 small bread pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Frost or drizzle with chocolate or vanilla icing.

title: corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl.
In another bowl, combine milk, butter and egg and blend well.
Slowly pour into flour mixture, stirring until blended. Stir in green chilies.
Spoon batter into lightly greased corn shaped molds.
Bake on lowest rack in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 sticks.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into crescents and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: whipped filling
directions: Cook flour and milk in small saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until very thick. Cool completely.
Cream the sugar, margarine, shortening and vanilla until fluffy. Add flour mixture and continue beating until consistency of whipped cream. Should be smooth, not grainy.
Freezes well.
Makes about 3 cups. Chopped dates, raisins, cherries, candied pineapple, nuts, etc., may be added for variety.
Use to fill cakes, etc.
This is like in Twinkies, but better.

title: barbecue bread spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread fairly thick on bread and put into oven to let it melt.

title: jerky
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix with meat.
Marinate in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight.
Drain in colander and take out peppers. Lay meat on oven racks to dry.
Set oven at 150°.
Leave door open a crack and leave meat in oven 6 hours.
Turn oven off and leave meat in for another 6 hours.

title: man-cooked meal
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in soup, chili sauce, chili powder, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Prepare corn muffin mix as directed on package. Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: liver pate
directions: Wash liver thoroughly and remove as much of gray membrane as possible.
Grind together first 4 ingredients using fine blade. Put in large mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and blend well with large spoon.
Spoon into an iron pot or casserole with tight fitting lid.
Allow room for a slight swelling of pate.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, stirring well after 50 minutes.
Return to oven for 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven; spoon off excess grease and immediately pass pate through food mill (sometimes called a vegetable press) into another receptacle.
(This produces a smooth paste and leaves behind all liver membranes.)
Discard what remains in food mill.
Adjust seasoning to taste and mix thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator in tightly covered containers, until set, about 1 hour.
Serve cold on crackers.
May be safely kept for 2 weeks, properly refrigerated.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Mix and form into balls the size of small walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for one hour at 300°.
While still hot, shake in bag of powdered sugar.
When cool, shake again.

title: my mother's cheezy chicken soup
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients (cut up) in another pan until tender.
Melt butter or margarine; add flour, then add broth (preference of thickness depends on how much you use of the broth). Add Cheez Whiz.
Add cooked vegetables and chicken and broccoli; fold into broth and vegetables.
Let simmer.
Season with salt to taste.

title: fresh apple-nut bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Rinse cauliflower and place in bowl.
Cover and micro-cook on High for 3 minutes.
Turn cauliflower over and cook an additional 4 1/2 minutes on High.
Dice and set aside.
Micro-cook carrots and onion on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until tender.
Add cauliflower. Melt bacon drippings in Dutch oven.
Add flour and brown slightly. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables; heat thoroughly and season to taste.

title: italian haddock
directions: Cut fish in serving size pieces and place in baking dish. Sprinkle garlic powder, salt, pepper, parsley, oregano and green pepper on each piece of fish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top of fish.
Add tomato pieces, then mixture of tomato sauce and sauce from can of tomatoes.
Pour oil over all and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Baste once or twice during baking.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla well. Sift dry ingredients. Blend with first mixture. Mixture will be thick. Add apples and pecans. Coat well. Grease and flour Bundt pan (or tube pan or 9 x 12 sheet cake pan). Put in COLD oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (maybe a little less for sheet cake). Cool. Remove from pan. Glaze, if desired.

title: zucchini bread(sweet bread)
directions: Beat 3 eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
In large bowl, add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix the 2 together.
Stir and pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Combine berries, sugar, water, lemon juice and salt.
Divide into manageable portions and blend at high speed until liquified. Chill.
Just at serving time, mix the strawberry puree with the cream and grape juice.
Serve with a few chopped berries floating in each bowl.
If a less caloric soup is preferred, substitute yogurt or omit cream altogether.
Top with Creme Fraiche.

title: impossible chicken broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 aluminum 1 1/2-inch deep pie plates.
Rinse frozen broccoli with cold water to thaw.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion.
Put in pie plate. Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over mixture in pie plate.
Bake until test middle comes out clean, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Take out and put remaining cheese on top and place back in oven until cheese melts.
Let cool a little bit before serving.

title: homemade orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Melt butter; cream with sugar in large bowl.
Add egg and yeast to creamed mixture. Add flour and stir well.
Place in airtight container.
Store in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, stir down.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into bite-size pieces; mix.
Blend salt, celery seed, sugar and vinegar.
Place vegetables in a large bowl and pour in liquid.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach stuffed flounder
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine, cook spinach and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove skillet from heat; stir in pepper, bread, 1/4 teaspoon of paprika and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream

margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy. Add flour and baking powder; mix well. Chill dough for 2 hours or overnight. Roll out on a lightly floured surface until 1/8-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutter. Place on baking sheet (ungreased). Bake in 375° oven until lightly brown about 10 minutes. Cool before storing. Two cookies equal 58 calories.

title: baked corn
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain grease.
Layer 1/2 of corn in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Next, layer sausage and white sauce. Repeat with remainder of corn, sausage and white sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and egg in bowl.
Pour mixture into the pan with melted margarine.
Now spoon peaches (or fruit) over the top of mixture and put in oven.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes.

title: chicago style italian beef
directions: Mix beef, celery, onions, sweet pepper, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook in saucepan until meat is tender.
Add package of gravy mix, dry.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain and then mix all ingredients together, including broccoli.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add flour and eggs, then add salt and vanilla flavor.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 or 20 minutes, depending on oven.

title: old south salad
directions: Cook peas slightly and drain.
Dice celery and onions. Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut patty
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil; add peanuts and food coloring.
Cook over medium heat to a hard boil stage.
Take off heat and add butter and salt.
Beat until thick and pour into well-greased pan (round pizza pan).
Leave whole or break into pieces.

title: easy caramel corn
directions: In large roasting pan, combine corn and nuts.
Place in 250° oven while preparing glaze.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir sugar, Karo, margarine and salt.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over warm popcorn and nuts; stir to coat well.
Bake in 250° oven, stirring occasionally, 1 hour.
Cool; break apart.
Store tightly covered.

title: beef rouladen(contest winner)
directions: Pound meat very thin until almost double in size.
Salt and pepper.
Saute bacon and onion.
Spread 1 tablespoon of bacon mixture on each slice, spreading evenly.
Roll meat slices and tie with butchers string or secure with toothpicks.
Heat oil or drippings in large skillet.
Fry rolls until brown.
Reduce heat to low and add water and bouillon until covered.
Cover and cook until tender, approximately 1 hour.
Remove rolls from pan.
Skim off any fat.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour to little water until smooth.
Add to skillet and cook until thick.
Add salt and pepper as needed.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Return rolls (without picks or string) until warm.
Do not boil.

title: party punch
directions: Mix orange juice, sugar and tataric acid together.
Add enough water to make a gallon.
Mix well.

title: sweet 'n sour ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients and make balls.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Stir in sauce, onion and brown sugar. Place each biscuit in a greased muffin cup, pressing around bottom and up sides. Spoon mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 10 servings.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and melted butter and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt butter with
chocolate.
Over
low
heat,	combine sugar, flour, eggs and
vanilla.	Mix
together
with
melted butter and chocolate.	Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Drain peppers; remove seeds.
Put peppers, chopped onion
and diced garlic buds in blender; mix well.
Grate cheese with mayonnaise and salt.
Use mixer to combine cheese mixture.
Blend peppers, onion and garlic buds 4 to 5 minutes on high until fluffy.
Put in covered container.
Keep in refrigerator for a week before eating.
Will keep 3 months.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Combine beef mixture and all other ingredients.	Stir well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rice and beans with sausage
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and brown.
Remove sausage to paper towel.
In the same skillet, saute onion, pepper and garlic. Add tomatoes, salt, oregano and Tabasco; bring to boil.
Stir in rice and beans.
Remove from the heat and let stand 10 minutes. Fluff rice mixture.
Spoon onto a serving plate and arrange sausage on top.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and eggs until smooth.
Add dry cake mix and milk.
Blend until moistened and beat as directed on cake box. Divide batter into 3 parts.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
To 1/3 add strawberry Nestle Quik.
Add to pan.
Add vanilla to 1/3; pour over strawberry batter.
Add chocolate Nestle to 1/3; pour over vanilla batter.
Even top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chocolate espresso cake
directions: Melt chocolate	and
butter
together slowly; add sugar and coffee.
Heat
until
sugar
melts.
Beat eggs well, separately. Mix into chocolate mixture and pour into pan.
Line a 9-inch spring-form
pan
with
aluminum foil; butter and flour the foil, then pour out excess flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes to	1 hour and 20 minutes.	(You want the crust like a brownie.) When
the
middle is firm like the side, take out of oven. Refrigerate.

title: easy applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix in order given:
white sugar, brown sugar, shortening, eggs, salt, soda, vanilla, flour,
oatmeal,
corn flakes, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions; cool.
Poke holes in cake and pour Kahlua evenly over top.
Soak overnight.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Use a large glass bowl to layer dessert in.
Crumble cake and put 1/2 on bottom of bowl.
Top with 1/2 of pudding, then Cool Whip, then Skors.
Repeat using remaining ingredients and top with Skor bars.

title: kool aid punch
directions: Makes one gallon. Add one carton orange sherbet right before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Tear apart cake into bite-size portions and mix with 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Mix together (with mixer):
sugar, 8 ounces Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Combine the sugar/cream cheese mixture with the cake.
Put into a glass serving bowl.
Put strawberry glaze on top, then put fresh strawberries on top of this.

title: baked oysters
directions: Cook onions in margarine over low heat until done, not brown. Add cubed bread.
Stir until bread cubes are coated with margarine. Add celery seed, oregano, Lawry's salt, cracked pepper and salt. Put oysters into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add lemon juice. Sprinkle dressing mixture on top of oysters, pressing so bread mixture is between oysters.
Add bacon on top.
Bake in 425° oven until bacon is crisp.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Fold one chicken tender in half and wrap in one slice of dried beef.
Then wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around the beef and chicken. Repeat process until all tenders are used.
Lay wrapped chicken side by side in a medium size baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes in a 350° oven.
Melt the caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; spread over baked dough. Sprinkle the nuts and chocolate chips over the caramel layer. Drop remaining batter in spoonfuls on top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; lower to 325° when you put cake in oven. Combine margarine, cake mix and 2 of the eggs and mix well. Mixture will be stiff. Spread in long Pyrex pan (9 x 13-inch greased pan).
If pecans are used, sprinkle over cake now. Combine cream cheese, flavoring, confectioners sugar and egg.
Mix well and spread over pecans or bottom layer.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes before cutting.

title: dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sour cream.
Add the remaining ingredients and combine.
Hand mix; do not use blender.

title: potato chips
directions: Slice potatoes as thinly as possible.
Soak in cold water for 1 hour; drain and pat dry.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle chops on both sides with seasoning.
Brown in a skillet on both sides.
Remove chops.
Brown onion and bell pepper in same skillet until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add 2 cups of water.
Add 2 cups rice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 20 minutes.
Stir in onion and bell pepper to cooked rice.
Layer chops on rice mixture in a 3-quart dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin cupcakes
directions: Bake in muffin pan at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: fabric softener sheet replacement
directions: Once in a while, add 1 cup table salt to hot fire in fireplace or wood burning stove.
Burn potato peelings whenever you have potatoes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy and light.
Add sugar, then vanilla. Sift together the dry ingredients; beat into batter.
Scald milk and margarine together.
Blend this into the cake mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, or serve with strawberries or other fresh fruit.
This is like a pound cake.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Dice peaches, reserving several slices for garnish. Mix peaches and 2 tablespoons of the sugar in large serving bowl. Mix sour cream, remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon in another large bowl. Gently stir in whipped topping. Sprinkle 3/4 cup of the granola over peaches. Top with whipped topping mixture. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup granola. Garnish with additional whipped topping, reserved peach slices and cinnamon sticks. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion in skillet; drain. Boil egg noodles.
In large casserole dish, add ground beef, onion, bell pepper, Ragu sauce, whole tomatoes, egg noodles, mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Add Cheddar cheese and Swiss cheese to top of the ingredients.
Bake in oven until cheeses are melted.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder alternately with sour cream. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet, two-inches apart.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake until brown around the edges at 400° for approximately 10 minutes. Cool and store in airtight tin.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour. Add milk gradually, then add cheese.
Add Accent, salt, pepper and mustard to taste.
Add crab (after fully cooked). Cook until warmed through, then top with grated cheese and 1 package Ritz crackers.
Bake an additional 30 minutes until brown or cheese has melted.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Mix preceeding.
Garnish with patience, smiles and kisses. Sprinkle well with sense of humor.
Wrap in love and bake in a steady fire of devotion.
Serve in generous portions each day.

title: mrs. lynche's creamy frosting
directions: Cream margarine and confectioners sugar with electric mixer on low.
Add heated cream until blended.
Add vanilla; mix well.
May add more or less cream for desired thickness.
This frosting is good on any basic cake from mix.

title: pasta house salad
directions: Break lettuce into desired pieces.
Chill with remaining ingredients.
Add dressing, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Toss and serve chilled.

title: kristen's crispy homemade waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg yolks, water and oil. Whip the egg whites.
Add last.
Batter should be thin.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Top with fresh or frozen strawberries.

title: boned chicken with dried beef
directions: Grease pan (9 x 13-inch or lasagna pan).
Line pan with dried beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon.
Mix sauce (soup, sour cream and wine).
Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Uncover and bake 3 hours at 275°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: wild rice portuguaise
directions: Soak rice overnight; drain and wash.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole, cover and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Good with fried fish.

title: black eyes of texas casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet, stirring frequently; drain.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Layer ground beef mixture and tortillas alternately in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, ending layers with ground beef mixture.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake; mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, building up slightly around edge of pan.
Bake 10 minutes until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Drizzle over apples.
(Topping will not completely cover apples.)
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together; mix well.
Add enough mayonnaise for desired moisture.

title: creamy tater soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except milk. Cook until vegetables are very tender, about 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Transfer to blender and blend until smooth.
Stir in milk.

title: flavorful mandarin cooler
directions: In a blender, combine milk, orange juice, orange yogurt, pudding mix and ice cubes.
Cover and process for 20 seconds until smooth.
Stir before pouring into chilled glasses.

title: white cake with caramel icing
directions: Beat 2
more
minutes.
Bake in two layer pans, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the margarine and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Add 3/4 cup white sugar and all the brown sugar.
Stir in egg, vanilla, salt, baking soda and flour.
Hand roll dough into 1-inch balls and then roll the ball in remaining (1/4 cup) white sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet, flatten slightly.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Remove cookies from oven and gently place Hershey kiss on each cookie.
Press into cookie just enough for the cookie to "crack".
Bake an additional 2-4 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and ENJOY!
Makes 5 dozen!

title: chicken in lemon butter
directions: Place chicken in flat baking dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Baste frequently with sauce from bottom of baking dish.

title: bumsteads
directions: Toss ingredients lightly.
Fill 8 hot dog rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well until blended. Spoon into a 10-inch quiche dish or deep-dish pie plate. Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: caramel corn chex
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes (without stirring).
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over Corn Chex and pecans or peanuts.
Pour into large cake pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight containers.

title: devilish fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread frozen potatoes on cookie sheet. Heat for 15 minutes in hot oven.
While potatoes are heating, combine all seasonings, then stir in oil.
Take potatoes from oven and toss them with seasoning mixture.
Return to oven for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until brown.
Mix salad dressing, mayonnaise and sour cream in bowl and spread evenly on crescent rolls.
Garnish with vegetables and cheese and serve.

title: spaghetti amore
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease large casserole dish. Cook noodles as directed on package. Combine 1/2 cup cheddar cheese, soups and water in large bowl. Heat shortening in large skillet; cook meat, onion and bell pepper. Drain. Add cooked and drained spaghetti to soup mixture. Mix well. Add meat mixture to soup and spaghetti mixture. Mix well. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheddar on top of casserole. Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Cover at any point if noodles begin to dry. Cook until thoroughly hot and bubbling around sides.

title: old fashioned apple loaves
directions: Stir all ingredients in a large bowl with a spoon until well blended.
Divide batter evenly into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool loaves in pan on a rack about 2 hours before removing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick fix cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and
pour
over
melted margarine or butter. Heat the fruit and pour over top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour,
or
until
brown.
Fruit
that
can	be used are peaches, apples, blackberries, strawberries or cherries.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water and 7-Up; let gel slightly, then add marshmallows, crushed pineapple (drained) and bananas.
Cook the pineapple juice, sugar, egg yolk and cornstarch until thick and let cool.
Combine butter, cream cheese and Dream Whip (which has been mixed with 1/2 cup milk) to the mixture.
Spread topping on gelled mixture.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni and allow to cool slightly.
Mix with remaining ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute sausage and butter for 5 minutes.
Remove sausage and drain.
Saute vegetables in drippings for 5 minutes or until they begin to wilt.
Add sausage, beans and remaining ingredients. Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook rice according to package.
Serve red beans over rice.
Feeds 8 people.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Slice green pepper and onion.
Mix with carrots.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat just to a boil.
Pour over carrots.
Toss; then refrigerate overnight.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each egg. Add cream of tartar, soda and flour; mix well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Knead; roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham hodgepodge
directions: In large sauce pan or dutch oven, combine cabbage, carrots, potatoes, ham, onion, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until vegetables are done.
Add undrained beans and cook covered 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Add more water if necessary.
6 to 8 servings.

title: chess pie cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add instant Cream of Wheat to milk and sugar mixture and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Slowly add 6 eggs (well beaten) and beat while adding.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and refrigerate.
Serve cool.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Brown the chops first in a large frying pan. Remove from pan and set aside.
Add the soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce to drippings in pan. Stir all together thoroughly.
If you feel there is too much grease, pour off excess before adding soup, etc. Place chops in Pyrex dish and pour sauce over them. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour with cover on dish.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom

title: sesame cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumber, discard seeds, cut lengthwise in quarters and then dice to about 1/2-inch pieces.
Salt and let stand 5 to 30 minutes.
Drain the juices.
Chop green onions in 1/2-inch lengths. Dice onions and chop garlic (fine).
Mix all ingredients together and let stand at least 30 minutes before eating.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix ground beef and rice.
Season to taste.
Form 12 to 16 balls.
Place in large casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and water; pour over balls.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: easy cheesy chicken
directions: Place melted butter in baking pan.
Roll chicken in butter, then in cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese rice souffle
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and milk to make white sauce.
(I add 1/2 teaspoon mustard here.)
Cool.
Grate cheese.
Beat yolks to white sauce.
Add rice to white sauce.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold whites into mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased Pyrex dish or 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in medium oven at 375°.
There will be a groove that forms 1-inch from the edge.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together, putting in 3-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: hot rolls
directions: Boil water; add shortening until melted.
Add sugar and salt.

title: black bean chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Let eggs, cream cheese and margarine come to room temperature. Cream sugar, margarine and cream cheese together for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add large eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and then add small amount at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Pour into lightly greased Bundt or tube pan.
Place in cold oven and set at 300°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place peanut butter and marshmallows in a bowl.
Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage in cold water.
Remove from heat; pour over peanut butter and marshmallow.
Beat vigorously until smooth. Pour into an 8-inch greased pan.

title: baked steak
directions: Brown floured steak and drain meat, then layer with soups and mushrooms.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Break eggs into the pan you are going to cook in; add sugar and beat well.
Add juice and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When it boils, remove from heat and add jello.
Set aside until it begins to congeal.
(In the refrigerator speeds it up.) Place the 1 cup evaporated milk in a bowl in the freezer. When it gets ice crystals around the edge, whip it until it is stiff and add it to the jello mixture.
Fold it together well and fill your baked pie shells.
Chill until well set.
Makes one large or two small pies.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine crumbs, oleo, peanut butter and sugar. Work together until smooth with hands. Press mixture into a 12 x 18-inch buttered pan. Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Spread firm. Set out to room temperature before cutting into squares.

title: chicken and biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook onion, celery and green pepper in butter until soft.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add chicken broth and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Combine onion mixture with chicken and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Place in oven to heat while you make the biscuits.
Prepare biscuit mix and knead a few times.
Roll out and cut into 1-inch thick biscuits.
Place biscuits on top of hot chicken mixture and bake until biscuits are lightly browned, about 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: diet lemon pie
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together well.
Pour into crust; chill.

title: caramel german chocolate brownies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 3/4 cup softened margarine until smooth.
Melt caramels, 1/2 cup evaporated milk over low heat until creamy.
Put half of cake mixture into pan and bake for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and add chocolate chips over baked cake mix.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Drop remaining cake mix by spoonfuls over caramel mixture.
Bake 6 minutes. Remove from oven and spread over entire pan and bake for 13 minutes.

title: saltine heath bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with foil. Spread butter over foil.
Put 1 layer of saltine crackers over foil.
In saucepan, mix together brown sugar and butter. Bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chips. Spread chips over when melted.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds or finely chopped walnuts.

title: torta dolci(sweet torte bread pudding)
directions: *The bread can be a couple of days old; remove most of the crust.

title: beef fajitas
directions: In nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat; cook onion, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper, stirring often, for 5 minutes or until onion is softened.
Add beef and salsa; cook, breaking up beef with back of spoon, for about 3 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Add peppers and zucchini; cook, stirring for 3 minutes or until tender-crisp and liquid has evaporated.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Chop onions finely.
Reserve 1/4 chipped beef.
Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Roll into ball and cover with beef.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sandy's banana bread(low calorie)
directions: Combine bananas, egg whites and brown sugar in a large mixing bowl. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix with bananas, egg and brown sugar mixture.
Add melted butter.
Place mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken, bay leaves, 1 onion, garlic powder and soup base in a large pot with the water, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken and bay leaves.

title: poulet provencale(sauteed chicken with tomatoes)
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet and add chicken pieces, skin side down.
Cook over moderately high heat until golden brown on all sides.
Add mushrooms and keep cooking.
Add bay leaves, thyme, onion and garlic.
Cook, shaking the skillet often until other ingredients are equally distributed in and around chicken pieces.
When chicken has cooked (10 to 12 minutes), remove pieces to a serving dish.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in skillet with flour, stirring to blend evenly.
Add wine, tomatoes and broth.
Stir and bring to boil.
Return chicken to skillet, add anchovies, salt and pepper.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes.
Add olives and cook another 5 minutes.
Serve over rice, pilaf or noodles.
Yields 4 servings. Bon Appetit!

title: angel delight
directions: Melt chips and water in double boiler.
Stir in egg yolks and salt.
Beat egg whites and sugar.
Stir in cooled chocolate.
Whip cream and vanilla and fold into chocolate mixture.
Tear up cake and put in bottom of loaf pan.
Cover with chocolate mixture. Chill 6 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then at 300° for 40 minutes. Makes three 9-inch pies.

title: berry crumble
directions: Spread berries in square glass dish, 8x8x2-inch.
Sprinkle with juice.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over berries. Microwave uncovered on high 7-10 minutes or until berries are hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
May be baked in conventional oven 30 minutes at 375 degrees.
I have also made this with no margarine, and it is good for those on a low-fat diet.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender. Remove fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy hot and sour soup
directions: Thinly slice mushrooms. Slice meat and tofu into 1 1/2-inch strips about the thickness of a pencil. Chop green onions into small pieces. Bring soup stock to a boil. Add all ingredients (save aside the onions); simmer about 1 minute. Add wine, soy sauce and vinegar. Bring back to a boil. Add cornstarch paste to thicken soup. Remove from heat; add chopped pieces of onion.

title: texas rangers beef casserole
directions: One can of mushrooms can be used instead of tomatoes.

title: jumbo reese's
directions: In microwave bowl, microwave 1/2 cup margarine and peanut butter for 1 minute.
Stir.
Add powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Empty soups into pan.
Add 3 cans of water.
Heat and blend soups and water together.
Stir in rice when blended.
Drop in chicken breasts.
Cook at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: okinawan fried rice
directions: In large saucepan, bring to boil 1 cup rice in 2 1/4 cups water. Reduce heat to low heat and cook until all water is absorbed (approximately 20 minutes) or follow package directions. In large skillet, drizzle 1 to 2 tablespoons olive oil and fry the 4 pork chops. Cut chops into bite-sized pieces. Discard bones and pieces of fat. Add sliced peppers, onion and celery to skillet and cook with chops (pieces) until vegetables are tender. Add cooked rice to the ingredients in skillet; mix thoroughly. Break eggs into the skillet mixture and continue cooking mixture until eggs are cooked throughout the other ingredients, mixing as they cook. Add soy sauce and stir thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: rotel
directions: Put in 3-quart Pyrex dish with lid on and microwave for 6 minutes.
Stir and put back in for 3 minutes.
Uncover, remove and stir again.
Cool to room temperature with lid on.
Serve with veggies, chips or crackers.
Also good on baked potatoes.

title: fudgy chocolate ice cream
directions: In
large
mixer bowl, beat chocolate, Eagle Brand, egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in half and half, whipping cream and nuts,
if desired.
Pour
into
ice	cream
freezer.
Freeze according to instructions.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In electric mixer, beat peanut butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in confectioners sugar.
Slowly beat in milk.
By hand, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust; grate chocolate over pie and freeze overnight.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into foil muffin or cupcake liners, 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Cool.
The centers will indent.
Place a tablespoon of blueberry pie filling on each and refrigerate.

title: baked chicken pieces
directions: Rinse chicken pieces and set in colander to drain, then in large bowl, mix cracker meal and Lawry's seasoning.
Roll chicken in cracker meal mix and set aside.
In large bowl, mix eggs and Pet milk.
Roll chicken in egg mix, then thoroughly back in cracker meal and set on platter.
When done, cover chicken with wax paper and set in refrigerator for about 4 hours or overnight.
Brown in lard and set on a rack in a baking pan; add a little water.
Then cover with foil paper and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Let cool to warm temperature and serve.
Good for lunch or snacks for 3 days after preparing.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350°.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine orange juice, honey and lime juice. Pour over fruit mixture, tossing gently. Cover and chill 2 hours. Add bananas just before serving.

title: heloise famous fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in a large very heavy saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Let boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter.
Beat only until chips and marshmallows are melted.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in large ungreased pan.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Shake chicken in flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter in large 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Turn chicken in melted butter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Combine juice with sugar.
Pour over chicken.
Lay pineapple, onion and pepper on top. Bake about 45 minutes at 375° until done.
Baste occasionally.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into small pieces; brown in skillet.
Mix together remaining ingredients; pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: candied yams
directions: Pour yams into pot.
Add brown sugar and bring to a boil. Pour into casserole dish and add layer of miniature marshmallows. Bake in oven until marshmallows are brown.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and paprika.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles. Serves 3.

title: yellow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When done, punch holes.
Add coconut cream and crushed pineapple.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip and top with crushed pecans.

title: pizza
directions: In a large bowl, mix green pepper, onion, celery, olives, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce. Stir hamburger and pepperoni into the mixture. Mix well. Put on deep cookie sheet in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes. Pull out and sprinkle all over with cheese. Put back in oven until cheese melts. Good anytime - breakfast, lunch or dinner!

title: meat loaf (turkey)
directions: Brown onion in butter.
In large mixing bowl, place beef, turkey and pork.
To meat, add browned onions, bread crumbs, oat bran, bouillon, eggs and seasonings.
Mix together.
Form 2 loaves in 8-inch baking dish.

title: veal meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat oil in frying pan and add the onion.
Saute for 3 minutes and add the celery and carrot.
Saute for five minutes over medium-high heat.
Mix the vegetables into the ground veal.
Add the parsley, bread crumbs, nutmeg, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Lightly oil a baking dish.
Divide mixture into small individual loaves.
Place in baking dish and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ginger fruit crisp
directions: Drain the peaches and set aside.
Using a rolling pin finely crush the cookies in a plastic bag.
Melt the margarine.
Blend in the crumbs, nuts and brown sugar.
Arrange the fruit in a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle the crumb mixture over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm. Serves 6.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Place dough on baking sheet.
Place next 4 ingredients on dough, then place remaining ingredients on pizza.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy texas dip
directions: Drain picante sauce, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine picante sauce and sour cream.
Stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons reserved liquid.
Cover and chill.
Garnish, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar until smooth.
Add rice, drained pineapple, cherries and marshmallows.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well; add 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.
Chill.

title: broccolli casserole
directions: Cook broccolli as directed. Mix together cheese whiz, water, soup and rice. Add this to the broccolli in a greased casserole dish. Top with onions and Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 min, until sides are bubbly.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat.
In casserole dish, layer the following: meat, macaroni, pizza sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender; drain.
Mash potatoes, stirring in salad dressing, cream cheese, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Mash until light and fluffy.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake in 350° oven for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange tomato wedges, mushrooms, olives and artichoke hearts on top.
Pour dressing over vegetables and chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Cook linguine according to package directions. Place in deep platter.
Arrange chicken and vegetables on top; be sure to use juice.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with fork.
Add sugar, flour, milk, butter and cream.
Pour over unbaked rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 300° until brown and done.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pastry shell. Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and cocoa. Add eggs, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake 60 minutes.
Cool completely. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together 2 cups flour, butter and confectioners sugar and press into bottom of 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar the night before.
Mix with broccoli and raisins.
Add bacon bits just before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add vinegar and salt; mix.
Bake in pie crust for 10 minutes at 250° and then at 300° for another 20 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Roll and spread with granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: angel's peanut butter cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
Add the dry ingredients.
Beat until well moistened.
Spray 9 x 13 inch cake pan lightly with non-stick cooking spray.

title: chocolate chocolate cake!
directions: Combine first four ingredients, beating well.
Mix in other ingredients. Pour into greased, oblong pan. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: moist carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well. Add pineapple, carrots, oil and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts. Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° approximately 1 hour or until done tested with a dry toothpick.

title: baked bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, sugar and sprinkling of cinnamon.
Set aside.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Add the bread cubes.
Pour egg mixture over cubes and let cubes soak up the liquid.
You can add a few chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until firm.
Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in applesauce.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir into sugar and shortening mixture.
Add raisins, nuts and oats. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: indian chocolate cake
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add cocoa and mix.
Add coffee, mix slowly.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Beat 1 minute.
Add boiling water.
Mix slowly until well blended.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, frost.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and spread onto a pizza pan with your fingers.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: purple passion
directions: In pitcher, combine all ingredients, except ice, grapes and mint.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cover and chill.
Serve over ice; garnish with grapes and mint, if desired.
Makes 1 quart.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well, cover.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: wedding punch
directions: Defrost frozen juices.
Mix everything but ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 75 to 100.

title: sweet and sour	meatballs
directions: Mix the above and make into small meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet and brown in 400° for about 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to simmer jello and pineapple, then add sugar, baby food and cream cheese.
Cook until cream cheese melts.
Chill 1 hour. Whip Carnation milk until frothy and fold into salad.

title: chocolate eclair delight
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with whole crackers.
Mix pudding as for pie, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half over crackers, and then another layer of graham crackers, and then the rest of the pudding mix.
Add another layer of crackers.

title: kahlua white russian cake
directions: Combine Kahlua, vodka and chocolate.
Place over low heat until chocolate melts.
Cool slightly.
Resift flour with baking soda and baking powder.
Grease well and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in chocolate mixture then flour mixture.
Divide batter into two pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out on racks to cool completely.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat juice and seasoning to boiling and pour over lemon flavored gelatin.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Chill.
Pour into molds that have stuffed olives.
Cut crosswise or pimiento strips in the bottom.
Serve with mayonnaise on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pickle relish
directions: Very finely chop all vegetables except cucumbers and place in glass bowl (not metal).
Mix in salt and let set overnight.
Chop cucumbers and put in cold water and let set overnight.
Next day drain all vegetables and mix with remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Store in hot sterilized jars.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ginger ale.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Garnish with cherries, orange and lemon slices.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.
Serves 40 to 50 cups.

title: best veggie dip
directions: Mix in food processor.
Makes approximately 1 pint of the best vegetable dip ever.

title: my mom's baked potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with bay leaf and salt.
Cool, peel and dice. Place in 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, butter, salt, pepper, onion and 1 1/2 cups cheese. Top with 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine lettuce, cauliflower and onion.
Top with bacon. Combine mayo, cheese and sugar and frost top of salad.
Cover bowl and store in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: meat gravies for roasts
directions: Natural Gravy is easy to make.
Let drippings in pan cool. Pour off most of fat, but keep brown drippings.
Add water.
Season to taste and heat.
Serve hot.

title: spinach quiche(low calorie)
directions: Use a fork to make holes in pie shell.
Brush shell with egg mixture.
Blend egg and Egg Beaters.
Bake shell at 350° for 5 minutes.
Thaw spinach and drain very well; pat between paper towels to get it dry.
Saute onion in spray coated skillet.
Mix onion and spinach and spread in bottom of pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over spinach.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: no-crust fudge pie
directions: Place chocolate squares and margarine in saucepan.
Heat on low until melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and pecans to chocolate mixture.
Stir until completely mixed.
Grease a long pie pan with margarine.
Pour mixture into pan.
Place into cold oven; turn oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: lemon cake
directions: Follow cake mix directions and mix together first 5 ingredients.
Put into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Mix powdered sugar, lemon juice, butter and hot water.
When cake is done, remove from oven.
Pierce cake all over with meat fork.
Spoon lemon mixture over cake.

title: pump house stew
directions: Place in a casserole or roaster by order listed, except the wine, which is added last hour of baking.
Cover tightly and place in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Open and stir well from the bottom. Return to oven and bake 5 hours total.
Add the red wine during the last hour of baking.
Serves a crowd.

title: cucumber snacks
directions: Beat cream cheese, Italian dressing mix and mayonnaise until fluffy.
Spread generously on cocktail rye bread and top with cucumber slice.
Stack on plate; cover and refrigerate.
You may want to double the recipe!

title: homemade rolls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let raise and pinch into small portions. Put in bread pan.
Let raise and bake from 10 to 15 minutes, until top turns brown.

title: holiday fruit bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together next 3 ingredients and add. Mix nuts, raisins, bananas, and candied fruit and add.
Mix well. Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: good orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple; to the juice, add enough water to make 2 cups.
Dissolve marshmallows and gelatin in boiling juice.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Whip cream; to it, add mayonnaise. Into this mixture, crumble cream cheese or dice very fine.
Add pineapple pieces.
Fold into gelatin; chill until firm.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Trim chops and brown on both sides.
Place in pressure cooker or covered casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with lemon slices and onion rings.
Pour over catsup and water.
Cook in pressure cooker for 15 minutes at 10 pounds or in covered casserole 1 hour at 350°.
Potatoes may be quartered or halved and cooked with the pork chops if desired.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large salad bowl; toss with Poppy Seed Dressing.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff iii
directions: Wash and cut mushrooms.
Season meat and brown in butter. Transfer to casserole.
Brown mushrooms in same pan and put them in casserole.
Put flour into remaining juices in pan and add sour cream.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over meat.	This can be prepared the day before.
Casserole should be heated in a very low oven (250° to 300°) for 1 hour.
Serves 8.
Serve with rice or English muffins.

title: chili
directions: Do not brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix these ingredients well and spread in a small square pan.

title: marinated pork kabobs
directions: Combine ketchup, lemon juice, brown sugar, soy sauce and minced onion in a bowl.
Cube pork and marinate for at least 30 minutes or overnight.
Remove meat from bowl.

title: potato dough baked goods
directions: For doughnuts, cinnamon rolls, sticky buns, dinner rolls and coffee cake.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix milk, potatoes, butter and sugar in large bowl.
Let cool, then add yeast mixture and 6 cups flour.
Let stand until mixture foams up (about 20 minutes). Add eggs, salt and additional 11 to 12 cups flour.
Dough should be soft.
Turn out on floured board and knead until satiny.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Form as desired. Serves 100.

title: bubble bread
directions: Melt together slowly over low heat. Pour in greased, small square pan or use PAM.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, water and salt to rolling boil.
Place 1 head of dill and 1 bud of garlic in quart jars.
Warm cucumbers in very hot water.
Place warmed cucumbers in jars.
Pour boiling solution over cucumbers and seal while hot.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: chocolate dipped nuts
directions: Stirring constantly, melt chocolate in a small saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add about 1 cup nuts to chocolate, stirring to coat well.
Remove nuts individually with fork. Place on waxed paper.
Repeat with remaining nuts.
Allow chocolate to harden.
Store in a cool place (don't refrigerate). Yields 4 cups nuts.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Set aside.
Heat the sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over the carrots, peppers and onion.
Store in refrigerator until seasoned through.

title: chocolate chip sour cream bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix in sour cream. Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Lightly stir in chocolate chips.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until done.
Cool.
Cover loosely with foil.

title: ricotta-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove mushroom stems and chop.
Combine stems and next 7 ingredients; mix well.

title: chutney dip
directions: In a food processor, combine Ricotta and cream cheese. Process until smooth.
Transfer to a small serving bowl.
Stir in curry powder and salt.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Prepare fruit (approximately 2 pounds cranberries), 3 1/4 cups water and 1/4 cup vinegar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes; add spices.
Measure 7 1/2 cups fruit into a 6 or 8-quart saucepan.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Stir oil and milk together, then add to mixture.
Pat in pie plate.
Prick crust.
Bake at 425° until slightly browned.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken breasts (I usually pound them flat).
Put one slice Mozzarella and 1 slice baked ham on each breast.
Roll and put in a toothpick.
Dip each into melted butter and roll in Parmesan cheese and bread crumb mixture.
Place in glass baking dish and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese; stir until melted.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch or 10 x 6-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: crunch clusters
directions: Mix together 2 cups Cap'n Crunch, Rice Krispies and peanuts. Melt white almond bark according to directions.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Add 3 more cups of Cap'n Crunch.
Mix well and pour onto large cookie sheet with sides.
Refrigerate until firm. Break up into small pieces.

title: chili max
directions: Cook kidney beans, tomato sauce and tomato soup.
Add chili powder to sauce.
Fry hamburger and strain.
Add beef to sauce. Pour over cooked creamettes.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Place all in blender, blend on high until all strawberries are crushed and mixture is thick and slushy. Serve with a spoon. Makes 1-2 servings. Cool and
refreshing.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of bread cubes into greased pan.
Cut cream cheese into cubes and sprinkle half over bread.
Repeat layering with bread and cream cheese.
Whip eggs, milk and maple syrup and pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon velvet cake
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Bake 325° till done.

title: pastel mint dessert
directions: Crush cookie and place half in bottom of a 9 x 13 pan.
Whip cream, fold in mints and marshmallows.
Spread whipping cream mixture over cookie crust. Top with remaining cookie crumbs. Cover and refrigerate 2-3 days.

title: bread stuffing(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter.
Add to bread crumbs and seasonings.
Toss with enough liquid to moisten.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: perfect seafood salad
directions: Thaw crab or shrimp if using frozen.
Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve on lettuce, crackers or bread.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, adding to dry ingredients with melted shortening.
Should be a real soft dough; add a little more flour if you want to. Don't knead.
Flatten to about 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Let rise for 1 hour and then bake in a 425° oven until light brown.

title: glazed onions
directions: Peel onion and cut in an "X" in center of top.
Spoon sauce over top and cover.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes (per onion).
Check for doneness.
Makes 1 onion.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Cook 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies. Stir until well coated.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cooled.
Makes 24 squares.

title: biscochitos(spanish sugar cookies)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar and lard until creamy.
Add eggs and anise seed and cream again until very fluffy.
Mix with first mixture.
Add water, enough to hold dough together.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in shapes.
Dip tops of cookies in cinnamon and sugar (using the 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon).
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 400° about 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and applesauce.

Mix well. Sift together flour and soda; add cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg. Slowly mix flour mixture into wet ingredients until well blended. Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan that is greased and floured at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
In a large skillet, cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in margarine or butter until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, parsley, salt, paprika, red pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir together cold water and cornstarch.
Stir cornstarch mixture and shrimp into tomato mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir about 2 minutes longer or until shrimp turns pink.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: filled meat loaf
directions: Press half of ground beef (1 pound) into a greased pan. Moisten stuffing mix and spread over ground beef.
Add another layer of ground beef (1 pound), being careful to cover all of the stuffing.
Mix dry onion soup and mushroom soup with 1/2 can water.
Pour over ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions, saving juice.
Combine with juice and other ingredients.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put in jars; seal at once.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and baking soda.
Mix flour mixture with first 4 ingredients and add mashed banana and chopped nuts.
Pour into cupcake molds and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: krispie date bars
directions: In a saucepan simmer the butter and dates. Cover and simmer until soft, about 15 minutes. Add the Rice Krispies and walnuts. Pack into small pan. Cut into squares. Chill and store in refrigerator.

title: easy brunch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Combine water and raisins and boil until water is absorbed. Combine other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add raisins and pecans.
Bake in 12 x 7-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: To mix:
Take large glass dish, crumble cake in bowl.
Mix strawberries and Jell-O together.
Pour over cake.
Let harden. Mix frosting.
Put on top.
Approximately 198 calories per serving.

title: bishop bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and flour.
Then add Baker's chocolate.
Cut in large pieces, nuts and dates.
Don't cut cherries.
Bake in a lined bread pan at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Christmas treat.

title: flat bread
directions: Mix and roll thin on floured board. Brown both sides on pancake griddle and transfer to cookie sheet in 300° oven for a few minutes to harden.
Break into pieces and use as crackers.

title: quiche filling
directions: Add all ingredients together (except pie crust) and mix well. Pour into a lightly baked pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mincemeat for pies
directions: Cook meat until soft.
Add sugar, wine, spices and apples and cook about 2 hours.
Then add the cherries.
Bring to full boil. Can be frozen or canned.

title: easy chocolate drops
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together, blend.
Mix nuts and noodles into chocolate mixture.
Spoon onto wax paper and freeze for 5 minutes.

title: orange sponge cake
directions: Beat yolks until thick and lemon colored; add sugar gradually and 2 tablespoons of juice.
Blend well.
Add remaining juice alternately with sifted dry ingredients, mixing until smooth after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 9-inch ungreased tube pan in slow oven, 325°, for 1 hour.
Invert pan to cool.
Cover cake with boiled frosting and sprinkle grated rind of 1 orange over frosting before it sets.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Mix together with fork until coarse; chill mixture 1 hour and roll into rope 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 4-inch pieces.
Roll in Parmesan cheese or wheat germ.
Bake at 500° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: one hour rolls
directions: I use self-rising flour and omit baking powder and salt.

title: hot tuna buns
directions: Spread mayo on all bus. Sprinkle each half with tuna, pickles and onions. Spoon mayo over all. Sprinkle on cheese. Broil until brown.

title: daddy's tomato soup
directions: Mix tomatoes, margarine, sugar, salt and pepper in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour milk in.
Stir and bring to a second boil. Cover and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: jerky
directions: Mix salt and vinegar; bring to a rolling boil.
Drop meat in for 30 seconds or until meat turns white.
Drain and blot meat dry.
Mix garlic powder, red pepper (cayenne), garlic salt and liquid smoke well.
Brush mixture on meat.
Put in oven and bake at 175° for 2 to 3 hours.
If making at night, it is best if left in oven overnight after oven is turned off.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot and serve with tortilla chips hot.
Serves 15.

title: inez's quik-n-easy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set over night.

title: mushroom vegetable mix
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook eggplant with garlic and oregano 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low, cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, simmer 5 minutes or more until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: peanut krispies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil, then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Put in large 13 x 9-inch pan and press down.

title: stroganoff meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Add corn meal to the hot boiling liquid; stir vigorously until a thick mush is formed.
Add seasonings.
Cool; add egg.
Beat well and drop by rounded tablespoon onto a floured board.
Roll into small balls.
Dredge lightly with flour.
Drop into boiling turnip greens liquid and cook slowly for about 15 minutes.
Serve with greens.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix; heat until cheese is melted.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread. Spread slices with butter. Place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside. Cook sausage until brown, crumbling and drain well. Spoon over bread slices and sprinkle with dices of potatoes and grated cheese. Combine eggs, half and half and salt. Mix well and pour over cheese. Cover and chill overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 to 20 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine ingredients except butter and vanilla. Boil until the syrup barely forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat. Cool until lukewarm.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and stiff enough to spread.

title: aunt bedie's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar by hand. Add eggs. Mix in the dry ingredients (which have been sifted together).
Add vanilla.
Roll out very thin and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake in a moderate 325° oven until cookies are a light brown. Makes many thin and crisp tea cakes.

title: veal stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 4-inch strips.
Brown in shortening.
Add onions. Cook until soft.
Combine all the rest, except noodles.
Add to meat.
Heat thoroughly, do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: hens and rice
directions: In skillet, melt butter; cook celery, mushrooms and white rice until golden.
Stir in wild rice; spread on bottom of roaster. Combine soup mix and water.
Pour over rice mixture.
Prepare Cornish hens; arrange on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
I cover with foil and remove to brown.
A nice holiday dish.

title: egg custard pie(my mother's recipe)
directions: Blend sugar and butter until smooth; mix in eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a pie shell.
Dot top with nutmeat.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° and bake until filling in center is shaky.
If center is solid, it is overcooked.
If pie browns too soon, cover with foil.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease square cake pan.
In pan, put pineapple on bottom, then fruit pie filling.
Cover with yellow cake mix (straight from the box).
Slice butter thin and place all over top of dry cake mix.
Sprinkle vanilla on top. Place in oven and bake until golden brown.

title: peach crumbler
directions: Arrange peaches into buttered 8-inch baking dish or pan. Sprinkle lemon juice over peaches; blend together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until consistency of coarse meal.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6, with vanilla ice cream.

title: julka's cherry nut cake
directions: Put ingredients into a 9 x 13 inch ungreased pan, mix with fork, and bake in 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yummy-Yummy!!

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In separate small bowl, mix oil, vanilla, buttermilk and water.
Add all at once to dry ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 to 35 minutes or until done (top springs back).

title: chili burgers
directions: Brown beef, then add other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and bake at 350°.
Mix last 2 ingredients and use as topping.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spread crescent rolls into the bottom of a pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle sausage into pie pan.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, oregano, salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Bake about 40 minutes or until eggs are done.

title: squash pie
directions: Precook pie shell.
Lightly saute squash and onion in small amount of margarine.
Season to taste.
Mix eggs and half and half.
Layer ingredients into pie shell.
Can top with sliced tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes on bottom shelf of oven. Slice and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Separate juice from fruit and pineapple.
Cut oranges and mix with fruit and pineapple.
Combine juice, Tang and dry pudding in medium size bowl.
Dice apples and bananas in juice.
Stir and let set for a brief period.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: basic sweet roll dough
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
