Add flour to make a thick batter; mix well.
Add yeast and eggs; beat well.
Add more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board; knead until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down. Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into tea rings, rolls or coffee cake. Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for coffee cake, 25 for rolls or 20 minutes for individual rolls.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1 cup warm water, yeast and flour.
Cover bowl and let stand for 30 minutes.
Add rest of water, flour, shortening and sugar.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Let rise 2 hours before cooking.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, mix dry milk, peanut butter and honey. Roll dough into balls. Roll the balls in coconut. Makes about 24 kisses.

title: pizza cookie
directions: Line a 12-inch pizza pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil. Grease foil and set aside.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Put into greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes, tossed with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.
Turkey may be substituted for chicken.

title: broccoli casserole with onion rings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Drain broccoli and arrange evenly over bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
In small mixing bowl, blend soup and evaporated milk.
Pour mixture over broccoli and top with cheese. Bake 25 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven, top with onion rings and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mama bertha's fried peach pies
directions: Cook dried peaches in covered pan on low heat, using one cup of water until they are tender when cut with fork.
Remove from heat and drain.
Mash with fork and add sugar.
Set aside to cool.
Roll biscuits into circles (5-inch diameter), using flour on cutting board.
Place peaches on one half of biscuit.
Fold the other half over and use fork to seal the two curved edges together.
Fry on low heat in thin coat of oil until golden brown on one side.
Turn and cook on the other side, adding oil as needed.

title: orange sodas
directions: In each of 5 tall glasses, place 2 scoops orange sherbet. Pour in chilled carbonated orange beverage to fill glasses. Makes 5 servings.

title: cajun pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown the seasoned pork chops.
Place in large baking dish so that each chop will be on bottom.
Place 1 pepper ring on each pork chop.
Place large spoon of rice in bell pepper ring.
Pat until firm.
Put generous tablespoon of soup (undiluted) on rice.
Place a slice of onion and a slice of tomato on top.
Pour mashed tomatoes over chops and cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: creamy corn casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute celery, onion and red pepper in 2 tbsp. butter until tender.
Remove from the heat; stir in soup, corn, chestnuts and almonds.
Transfer to a 2 qt. baking dish.
Melt remaining butter; toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: no peek stew
directions: Add all vegetables to cut up stew meat in oven safe pot or deep casserole dish with lid.
Pour V-8 juice over ingredients. Add tapioca and stir.
Cook in oven 4 hours at 250.
Keep lid on tight and don't peek.

title: buttermilk shake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender container.
Cover and process on high until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 2 servings.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.
Use a big slotted spoon to mix the ingredients, using a sifting motion.
It is good either hot or cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch together in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until thick and clear, stirring constantly. Add strawberry gelatin.
Stir until dissolved and mixed.
Cool. Place fresh strawberries in baked pie shell.
(Use as many strawberries as you want.) Pour cooled gelatin mixture over berries.
Refrigerate for approximately 3 to 4 hours or until firm.

title: blueberry swirl ice cream
directions: In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Add 1 cup sugar and salt, beating until well blended; set aside.
In a medium saucepan over medium to low heat, bring 2 cups of the cream to just under boiling.
Gradually stir in 1/3 of hot cream into the yolk mixture until smooth, then stir back into hot cream in saucepan.
Stirring over low heat, cook until mixture coats a metal spoon and is slightly thickened.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In large bowl cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract; stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Turn mixture into pan.
Spoon pie filling into cake in 6 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until done.
Filling will sink into cake while baking. Place bottom side up on serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar if used.
Spoon Cool Whip on top if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan; add 1 cup sugar and peaches and juice. Bring to a steady boil.
Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, flour, milk and sugar.
Put the peach mixture in baking dish.
Add flour mixture; do not mix.
Just pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 package of chopped beef.
Shape into a ball and roll ball around in chopped beef.

title: chicken and seasoned flour
directions: Prepare seasoned flour.
Skin chicken and cut into serving size pieces.
Dredge well in seasoned flour.
In heavy skillet, over medium-high heat, melt margarine or butter.
Add chicken pieces and brown in batches if necessary on all sides.
When brown, transfer to roasting pan with tight fitting cover.
Pour beer over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is very tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Place carrots in serving dish. Set aside. In saucepan, put soup, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, vegetable oil and salt. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add onion and pepper. Pour over carrots. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in 1 1/2 quart glass casserole.
Microwave (High) 8 minutes, stirring once after 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave 2 minutes more. Stir in baking soda.
Pour onto greased baking sheet.
Stretch until thin, using 2 forks.
Cool and break into pieces.
Makes 3/4 pound.

title: ernestine's celery seed dressing for fresh fruit
directions: Mix dry ingredients and vinegar together.
Using an electric mixer slowly add Wesson oil, beating until smooth and all oil is added.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs. Add sugar and flour. Mix. Add other ingredients except pecans and mix. Add pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm. Cool and serve.

title: island teriyaki
directions: Mix, then soak meat for at least 2 hours (the longer the better). Broil or barbecue. Also may be used for stir-fry.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg with milk; stir in 1 tablespoon Crisco and corn.
Add combined dry ingredients and stir just enough to evenly distribute the ingredients.
Drop from tablespoon into Crisco oil; fry about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 12 to 16 fritters.

title: farmhouse potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornflakes and butter in large bowl. Place in 9 x 13 buttered pan. Mix cornflakes and butter and spread over potato mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar in bowl.
Blend in butter until a soft dough is formed.
If dough is too soft to handle, cover and chill.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll into coconut. Place 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: waldorf salad supreme
directions: Pour boiling water on lemon gelatin; stir until dissolved. Add 1 tablespoons of lemon juice; cool until almost congealed, then add chopped apples, celery and raisins.
Whip package of whipped cream until it forms firm peaks.
Fold in fruit and gelatin mixture.
Put in 1-quart mold and chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce with a few chopped nuts on top.

title: pork chops with baked beans
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place pork chops on bean mixture.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce and spread over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: beef and rice skillet supper
directions: Brown meat quickly in oil or to prepare with less fat, omit oil.
Drain oil from meat.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat until onion is tender.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Stir in green pepper; boil again.
Stir in rice; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rumble seat chili
directions: Brown meat in large skillet and drain.
Sprinkle with generous amount of chili powder.
Stir and cook an additional several minutes.
Put tomato juice, stewed tomatoes, beans and chili seasoning in large pot (5-quart) and heat on moderately high heat. Add meat, macaroni and onions (if desired).
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Stir frequently.
Add chili powder to taste and Tabasco sauce (if desired).
Cook at least 2 to 3 hours.
The longer it cooks the better it gets.

title: party potatoes
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Slice potatoes, sausage and onion thin then layer.
Cover with sliced or grated Velveeta. Cover with soup.
Then cover with foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fake potato salad
directions: Steam cauliflower.
Cut into small pieces.
Add all the ingredients except cream of mushroom supplement.
Mix Hi-Energy Cream of Mushroom Soup Supplement with liquid from steamed cauliflower to make 1 cup.
Stir soup mixture in lightly to ingredients.
tags: Hi-Energy Cream of Mushroom Soup Supplement

title: red velvet cake
directions: Have
eggs
and
buttermilk
at
room temperature.
Put Crisco and sugar into bowl and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and
keep beating.
Next mix red food coloring with cocoa, add to
butter mixture
with
vanilla and butter flavor and beat. Next
add
the flour,
salt and buttermilk in three portions, beating
after each addition, and beat until smooth.
Last mix soda
and vinegar together and blend into batter with a spatula,
do
not beat. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Wrap
a wet sweat band around the pan for even baking. Put in a 350° oven and bake for 40 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: ma's country meat loaf
directions: Combine chuck, onion, bread crumbs, egg, sour cream, catsup, mustard, parsley, salt and pepper in large bowl; mix well.
Spoon mixture in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease shallow 9-inch round baking dish.
Drain and squeeze out excess moisture from spinach.
Place in mixing bowl.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream, eggs, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Blend thoroughly and turn into greased dish. Bake 45 minutes or until firm and puffy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in corn meal.
Add milk to beaten egg and stir into first mixture. Add shortening and blend.
Turn into shallow greased 8-inch pan. Bake in hot 400° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy corn chowder
directions: Mix together with 2 1/2 to 3 cans of milk.
Heat to steaming. Be careful not to scorch.
Serves about 8.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on assorted crackers or cocktail bread.

title: excellent barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: mike's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers very thinly.
Add sliced onions and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover completely with cracked ice and then mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to a boil.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: doubletime pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until creamy.
Add syrup, sugar and 1 stick of melted butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine ingredients, except oil. Mix well.
Pour about 2-inches salad oil into a saucepan or frying pan and heat to 375°. Drop batter by tablespoons, 4 or 5 at a time, into hot oil.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Yields about 24 puffs.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk and onions; add half of the cheese, half of the beef and also the can of mushrooms. When hot, add the noodles. When the noodles have softened, pour into a buttered casserole. Top with remainder of the cheese and beef. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix oil and buttermilk.
Mix water and yeast together, then add to oil and buttermilk mixture.
Add dry ingredients; let mix for 15 minutes on low.
Can add cheese, if desired.
Shape into biscuits.
Brush tops with butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Slice unpeeled apples; cook until they are tender and run through colander.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook in covered pan or roaster in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until a small amount of the mixture will hold its shape when cool.
Stir down from the sides 2 or 3 times during the process.
The Apple Butter does not stick to the pan or scorch.
It does beautifully cooked in crock-pot 5 or 6 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar; sift salt, baking powder and flour together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour and milk.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: leigh's twice baked potato casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes as you would for mashed potatoes.
Mash and add mayonnaise, sour cream, milk, eggs, mustard and parsley. Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan and Cheddar on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: latkes(potato)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop mixture by tablespoon onto a hot skillet generously greased with butter or shortening.
Fry on both sides until brown.
Serve hot with sour cream or with applesauce.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo and mix with other ingredients.
(Chopped shallots or mild onions are optional.)
Bake in muffin pans sprayed with Pam at 400° until done and slightly brown.

title: one pan ham leftover skillet
directions: Fry potatoes and onion in butter and vegetable oil in large skillet, until browned.
Add ham, corn, salt and pepper.
Stir well, cooking on medium, 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Lay sliced cheese over top of skillet and cover for 5 minutes.
Uncover and fold cheese into dish with wooden spoon.
Serves 4.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place butter on large jelly roll pan. Heat in oven until melted; set aside.
Pare potatoes and quarter lengthwise.
In a large plastic bag, combine cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Shake to coat.
Place potatoes in butter on pan. Cook 1 hour and turn halfway through cooking.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread in a baking dish.
Spread broccoli on top.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, add more grated cheese and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese on top is melted and bubbly.

title: committee's corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cover corned beef with water.
Cook until almost done.
Add vegetables and simmer until done.
Slice corned beef thin; serve with horseradish, if you prefer.

title: vanilla balls
directions: Cream the butter.
Beat in cream and vanilla.
Sift together the flour and superfine sugar.
Add this gradually to the creamed mixture.
Mix in the chopped walnuts or pecans.
Chill.
Pinch off in pieces and roll into small balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderately slow oven, 325°, for 20 minutes.
Take from baking sheet and roll in vanilla sugar. Yield:
3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crush corn chips and place in casserole. Brown meat and mix with beans. Pour over chips. Pour undiluted soup over meat mixture. Pour sauce over meat and soup. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot jezebel
directions: Mix preserves, horseradish, mustard and pepper. Store in a covered jar in the refrigerator. To serve, place 1/3 Hot Jezebel on cream cheese. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and boil in separate pan. Drain and add to soup pot.
Add vegetables, spices, tomato soup, water and V-8.
Liquid should be over tops of vegetables.
If not, add equal amounts of tomato soup, water and V-8.
Bring to boil and simmer 1 hour.
Add tomato paste; stir and serve.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, peanut butter and butter. Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Press half of the cake mix in ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove and let cool. Sprinkle with morsels and milk.
Add remaining cake mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Scald milk with onion, remove onion.
Thicken milk.
Stir constantly, cooking 20 minutes.
Cook tomatoes with sugar 15 minutes, add soda and rub through a sieve.
Combine mixtures and strain.
Serve hot.

title: easy barbecue pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with garlic powder and mustard powder. Brown and drain off all excess oil.
Add barbecue sauce and water. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter 2-quart casserole.
In a 2-quart saucepan, bring water to boil; mix cornmeal and salt.
Add in steady stream while stirring.
Lower heat and cook 1 minute, stirring to avoid lumps.
Beat in butter and milk until smooth. Pour into casserole and bake for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: monkey cake
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Roll in 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place by pieces (half of biscuits) in ungreased Bundt pan and pour half of following mixture over it.

title: cajun stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 325° until you can easily pierce with fork (about 1 1/2 hours).
Cut lengthwise and scoop out pulp, leaving enough to hold shells firmly together.
Whip potatoes with margarine, cream, Cajun seasoning, onions, meat and cheese. Refill shells with mixture.
Reheat at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and dill weed.
Spread on baked crust while still warm; sprinkle with vegetables.
Pat slightly. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into squares, tiny pieces or flowerets.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cake
directions: Layer in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan, Rhubarb, Jell-O, sugar and marshmallows.
Make the yellow cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and turn upside down on platter.

title: apricot cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust for 9-inch nonstick spring-form pan.
Cut each apricot half into 5 slices and set aside.

title: slim-trim dressing
directions: Combine cornstarch and mustard in a small saucepan; gradually stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mix thickens.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator.
Shake well before use.

title: crunch bars
directions: With mixer, mix together margarine, sugar, eggs and salt. Gradually add flour, baking powder and pecans.
Spread on large, greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread marshmallows over the top.
Return to oven until the marshmallows are slightly melted.
Mix chocolate, peanut butter and cereal. Spread over marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: wax beans
directions: In a medium skillet saute onion until soft in butter.
Add wax beans, salt and pepper.
Heat on low until heated through, stirring often.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Mix the ingredients together. They will stay fresh in an airtight container for up to 6 months.

title: turkey porcupines
directions: Mix turkey, rice, onion soup mix and pepper.
Form into small balls.
Brown in oil, turning frequently, until lightly browned. Using large pan, pour sauce and water into pan; add the meatballs and cover.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
The rice will stick out from the meatballs when done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, wash and slice potatoes. Cook until tender with salt. Drain. Put half of potatoes in 9 x 13 dish. Spread 1 can celery soup over potatoes. Dice onion real fine over soup. Put 1/2 package shredded cheese over onion. Put margarine over cheese. Put other half of potatoes over cheese. Put other can of soup over potatoes. Put rest of cheese over soup. Cook in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: new england dinner
directions: Dip roast in seasoned flour and brown in skillet.
Put roast in a Dutch oven or large pan with lid.
Cook 1 hour and add cabbage, carrots, whole onions and water to cover.
Cook 1 hour and then add potatoes; cook until tender.
Serve with each vegetable in its own dish and meat on platter.
The broth is great for gravy.
The leftovers from this dish makes a great vegetable soup; just add a few other vegetables and tomato juice.

title: home canned rotel tomatoes
directions: Press peeled tomatoes into pint jar; add 1 jalapeno pepper (split), add salt.
Seal jar.
Place in pressure cooker.
Bring pressure up to 5; turn stove off.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Combine first six items; make balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Drain.

title: snicker bars
directions: Mix ice cream, peanut butter, Cool Whip and pudding together. Add Grape-Nuts.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, eggs and flour.
Add milk, butter and flavoring.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl beat eggs at high speed until foamy (about 3 minutes).
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: oven chipped potatoes
directions: In a shallow baking dish, arrange potato slices in layers. Melt oleo in small saucepan; add onion, salt and pepper.
Brush or pour oleo mixture on potato slices.
Bake at 425° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are crisp and brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hummus(mashed chickpeas with sesame)
directions: Rinse chickpeas under cold water; mash in a bowl.
Add garlic, sesame and lemon juice and stir until smooth.
Chill.
Serve on flat plate with Syrian bread.

title: party punch
directions: In a punch bowl, add pineapple, Hawaiian Punch and finally the ginger ale.
May add ice at this time.
Refrigerate items until cold before preparation.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift into a bowl corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Melt butter and shortening.
Cool. Beat eggs lightly.
Add butter and shortening.
Stir in milk.
Add to dry ingredients and beat 1 minute until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Butter a loaf pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake 30 minutes or until bread comes slightly away from edge of pan and is golden brown.

title: chicken taquitos
directions: Spoon chicken onto tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Roll up tightly.
Secure with toothpicks.
Chill, sealed in plastic bag in refrigerator.
Deep fry until crisp.
Drain.
Serve with guacamole or salsa.

title: coffee cake
directions: Boil raisins and coffee for 5 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beaten well.
Add vanilla, spices and raisins. Add flour and nuts.
Mix and pour in tube pan.
Cook at 300° for 2 hours.

title: strawberry 7-up pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch and 7-up to a boil.
Cook until thick. Add jello.
Stir well.
Let cool.
Slice strawberries in each baked pie shell.
Pour topping over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Cook broccoli, carrots, onion and potatoes until soft in water that just covers the vegetables (add salt to taste).
Add cream-style corn, cheese, milk and margarine.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add milk to make desired thickness.

title: beef boat
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Hollow out loaf of bread (rye or pumpernickel is good).
Place dip in hollowed bread and use bread pieces for dipping.

title: instant turkey
directions: Mix rice, boiling water and instant minced onion.
Cover bottom of greased 14 x 9-inch casserole with rice mixture.
Place cooked turkey pieces over rice.
Sprinkle frozen peas over turkey. Combine soups and milk; pour over casserole.
Combine crushed crackers with butter; pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream 1 stick oleo, white sugar, 1 cup light brown sugar and eggs. In a separate bowl, sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed ingredients.
Add oatmeal.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
While cake is baking mix topping.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix half the dry cake mix, margarine, eggs and vanilla in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes (centers will be soft).
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate (do not dilute), sweetened condensed milk and Cool Whip. Stir until well blended. Pour into pie crust. Freeze for at least 4 hours. Serve frozen.

title: green bean swiss style
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add sour cream gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, stirring often.
Fold in green beans.
Turn into greased casserole. Grate cheese and sprinkle over beans.
Crush corn flakes, mix with butter and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds during last 10 minutes.

title: tortiere (pork pie)
directions: Cut up potatoes, cook in boiling water 20 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Brown pork and drain off fat.
Stir in next 6 ingredients, 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring often.
Discard bay leaf, stir in potatoes and let cool. Roll half the pastry into a 12 inch circle.
Line a 9 inch pie pan. Trim even with rim, fill with meat mixture.
Roll remaining dough, slit.
Place on top of filling and trim to 1/2 inch beyond rim. Seal, flute and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In stockpot, combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add noodles.
Simmer an additional 15 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with crackers and dot with oleo.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, until cheese melts and crackers are golden brown.

title: melt in the mouths
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Then beat until light.
Add sifted flour, dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix lightly.
Drop scant teaspoon onto a cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes.

title: garden deviled eggs
directions: Cut each egg crosswise in slices.
Scoop yolks out into small bowl and mash well.
Set egg whites aside.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix egg, milk, salt and bread crumbs.
Allow crumbs to soften thoroughly.
Combine with ground chuck and chopped vegetables. Shape into loaf and place in Crock-Pot.
Top with Ketchup and green pepper rings.
Cover and set on high for 1 hour then turn to low for 8-9 hours.

title: broccoli and beef cantonese
directions: Trim all fat from the meat, then slightly freeze.
Slice across grain into strips, 1 to 2-inches long and 1/8-inch thick. Mix water and cornstarch until smooth.
Add soy sauce, sherry, ginger and garlic powder.
In heavy skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil very hot and add half the beef, stirring constantly, until lightly brown.
Then brown the other half.
Remove from pan, add 1 tablespoon oil; add mushrooms and brown lightly.
Return meat to pan and add broccoli, chestnuts and cornstarch mixture.
Bring to boil while stirring until sauce is thickened and clear.
Stir in bean sprouts and onion.
Allow to heat and serve.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains about 266 calories per serving.

title: peach apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add and stir in cream cheese. Let cool and add baby food and crushed pineapple.
Fold in pecans and whipped topping.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pineapple spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put sliced spareribs in shallow pan. Combine pineapple juice, vinegar, brown sugar, ajinomoto, ginger, garlic, shoyu and salt.
Mix sauce with spoon until mixture is dissolved thoroughly.
Mix cornstarch and water; add to mixture. Pour over spareribs.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: aw gee, paw cheese ball
directions: With a fork, cream the cream cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients, reserving 1 cup of pecans.
Mix well by hand.
Let the mixture harden in the refrigerator for 45 minutes.
Remove and shape into a ball.
Roll in the reserved pecans.
Makes 1 really big cheese ball.

title: george washington's fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a wooden mixing bowl. Lightly stir in the separately beaten egg whites and yolks. Then blend in the milk. Sift the baking powder into the flour and stir this in. After these ingredients are mixed, stir in all the fruits and spices.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, cherry pie filling and almond extract until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into long pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Thaw strawberries.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Let cake cool.
In a large plastic bowl, crumble cake in chunks and layer on bottom.
Layer strawberries on cake and then layer
pudding on strawberries. Repeat.
Layer with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: 10 baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight and cook.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, sugar and cocoa. Add the buttermilk, oil, food coloring, vinegar and eggs. Pour into 3 (9-inch) sprayed pans. Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: menudo
directions: *This is
an 8 x 8 x 12-inch block of beef tripe, about 3 to 4 pounds.

title: african chicken
directions: Heat 1/4 cup oil in frypan.
Add chicken, onion and garlic and saute until crisp, turning evenly.
Sprinkle with flour and add next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and continue cooking another 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Just before serving, heat remaining 1/4 cup oil and saute bananas until golden.
Arrange chicken in center of platter; surround with potatoes and bananas.

title: pineapple gooey cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Stir well until blended.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 275° for approximately 60 minutes.
Frost while slightly warm.

title: miniature venison pizza
directions: Split muffins; butter them lightly and lay out on cookie sheets.
Warm 5 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and spread with pizza sauce.
Crumble meat over the sauce; pile on olives, mushrooms and grated cheese.
Return pizza to the oven and heat 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese in blender until smooth; add sweetener, lemon juice, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk and beat again. Pour into 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
This is a good light lunch.

title: date and nut balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add dates, sugar and the beaten egg.
Bring to boil and continue same for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the cereal, nuts and vanilla.
When cool, form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add the beaten egg and molasses and mix well.
Add the sifted dry ingredients to first mixture and blend together.
Chill dough for several hours.
Shape the cooled dough into small balls about the size of a walnut and dip the tops in sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator (at least 8 hours).
Bake in deep 2-quart greased casserole dish until golden brown.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl until well blended. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut onions in 1/2-inch slices or rings.
Cut steak in thin strips.
In large skillet (oven-safe), brown steak in oil over high heat.
Add onions and saute until tender and crisp.
Blend soup, sherry wine and liquid from mushrooms with garlic salt.
Pour over steak and add mushrooms.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add grits to 4 cups boiling water and boil 4 minutes.
Add butter and cheese to hot grits.
When grits are lukewarm, beat eggs in a separate bowl until frothy.
Pour eggs into tea cup. Finish filling cup with milk.
Add milk and egg mixture to grits. Pour into greased baking dish and top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese browns in 350° oven.

title: gentlemen prefer chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet with oil, salt and pepper with a little butter.
When brown place in baking dish.
Put remaining ingredients over chicken in the order given.
Bake uncovered at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: cheddarburger skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Drain. Stir in soups and water.
Add potatoes.
Heat; stir occasionally.

title: turkey cutlets with artichoke-cream sauce(low fat - low cholesterol)
directions: Place cutlets between 2 pieces of wax paper and pound with a meat mallet until thin.
Flour cutlets and brown them in a saute pan in 3 tablespoons of olive oil and 2 tablespoons margarine.

title: chicken 'n dressing
directions: Boil fryer, cool and debone.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dressing with melted margarine (take out 1 cup before mixing) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken on top of mixture. Mix soups and broth from chicken in bowl.
Pour all on top of layered chicken and dressing.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of reserved dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix the dry ingredients, then add butter, beaten egg yolks and milk.
Fold in the egg whites.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
Heat margarine in skillet, add meat and fry until richly browned.
Add onion and garlic, peppers, pimentos, celery, salt and pepper.
Add water and bouillon and cook 20 to 25 minutes until meat is tender.

title: summertime mincemeat
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large kettle.
Boil 5 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Good for pie filling.

title: eilene's cooked fruit salad dressing
directions: Take juice from fruit and mix with eggs, flour, sugar and margarine.
Cook until it thickens.
Let mixture cool, then pour over mixed fruit, bananas and marshmallows.
Fold in and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: double good macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper, hot sauce, onion and cheese in large bowl. Fold in macaroni.
Spoon into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly 45 minutes.
You can add 2 teaspoons Dijon mustard instead of hot sauce for variation.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta (chill).
Add
crabmeat,
shrimp, snow peas, green onions, tomatoes, black olives and spinach leaves.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in boiling water just to separate. Combine with mushrooms, water chestnuts, soup, cheese, salt and pepper. Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Spray the inside of a large brown paper bag with Pam.
Put popcorn in bag.

title: spinach pie
directions: Thaw and drain spinach thoroughly.
Cut cheese into small cubes.
Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon into a greased pie plate.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until set (slightly golden brown around edges).
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onions. Drain off excess grease. Add remaining ingredients and cook for awhile.

title: swiss chicken bake
directions: Cook onion in butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in mushrooms, sour cream, milk and sherry.
Add chicken and chestnuts.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with grated Swiss cheese, then add on top bread crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Place chicken breast halves in baking pan so they don't overlap.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream, sherry and drained mushrooms to make a sauce.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle
paprika over all.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve with noodles or as meal entree. Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, margarine and 1 egg; press into greased pan.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dump all ingredients except pecans into a large bowl and mix well.
Top with chopped pecans and refrigerate several hours.

title: noel chicken ala paris
directions: Place chicken breasts in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, including mushroom liquid and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Serve with sauce over each breast and rice of your choice.

title: e-z diabetic cheese pie
directions: Soften gelatine in juice.
Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend well.
Pour in 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate. Entire recipe contains 2 fruits and 12 ounces protein.

title: ham and cheese salad
directions: In food processor put bologna, cheese, celery, olives, and boiled eggs and blend.
In a large bowl, add salt, pepper, relish and onions.
Add mixture from processor.
Add mayonnaise until spreading is easy.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine
lemon	juice, honey, cornstarch and juice from can of pineapple in saucepan.
Bring to boil and let thicken. Cool. Arrange prepared
fresh
fruit
on	tray.
Dip fruit in sauce.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: *Sift flour again after adding baking powder and salt.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Beat eggs lightly with wooden spoon. Stir in sugar, salt and vanilla, then cocoa dissolved in melted shortening. Stir in flour and nuts. Do not beat at any time. Spread mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. DO NOT OVERBAKE.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Layer in buttered shallow dish: Oysters, crackers, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour whipping cream over all and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kong namul-korea(blanched bean sprouts)
directions: This is probably one of the most popular vegetables served at Korean meals, second only to Kimchee.
Blanch fresh bean sprouts in boiling water for 60 seconds.
Drain and rinse immediately with cold water.
Combine dressing ingredients.
Toss well drained sprouts and dressing together in a bowl.
Top with 1 fresh, finely minced scallion and 1/2 teaspoon white sesame seed.
Serve chilled as a side dish!

title: cascaron
directions: Mix mochiko,
sugar
and coconut together.
Add coconut milk; mix until
just
moistened.
Form dough into 1-inch size balls; roll in sesame seed.
Shape will be oval.
Deep fry for 3 to 4 minutes, until golden brown.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine rice and broccoli with butter while warm in large bowl. Melt the cans of soup, cheese whiz and milk over low heat; stir till smooth.

Combine soups with rice, broccoli mixture, add seasoned salt. Spray 9 x 13 casserole dish with cooking spray; pour in mixture and spread evenly; sprinkle with paprika for looks. Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
In medium skillet, saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add chicken and the rest of the ingredients, except macaroni and cheese, grated cheese and nuts.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add prepared macaroni and cheese.
Mix well.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle grated cheese and nuts on top.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: Combine green beans and peas and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, blending well.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Cover. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In medium saucepan, bring pineapple to a boil. Sprinkle in both packages of jello, stirring well.
Remove from heat.
Cool well. Add the buttermilk, stirring well.
Fold in the Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish and refrigerate until congealed.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine and beat until smooth the shortening, salt, lemon rind, nutmeg, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to egg mixture. Add milk and mix well.
Drop level tablespoon of dough on greased baking sheet.
Flatten cookies by stamping with a flat-bottomed glass covered with a damp cloth.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired. Press 3 raisins into each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.
